74 #define NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE (OR_INT_SIZE * 3)
75 #define NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE (OR_INT_SIZE)

77 #if defined (CS_MODE)

83 /*
84  * Flag to indicate whether we've crossed the client/server boundary.
85  * It really only comes into play in standalone.
86  */
87 unsigned int db_on_server = 0;
88 
89 #if defined(CS_MODE)
90 static char *pack_const_string (char *buffer, const char *cstring);
91 static char *pack_string_with_null_padding (char *buffer, const char *stream, int len);
92 static int length_const_string (const char *cstring, int *strlen);
93 static int length_string_with_null_padding (int len);
94 #endif /* CS_MODE */
95 #if defined (SA_MODE)
96 static void enter_server_no_thread_entry (void);
97 static THREAD_ENTRY *enter_server (void);
98 static void exit_server_no_thread_entry (void);
99 static void exit_server (const THREAD_ENTRY & thread_ref);
100 #endif // SERVER_MODE
101 
102 #if defined (SA_MODE)
103 //
104 // enter_server_no_thread_entry () - enter server mode without getting a thread entry (e.g. when "starting" server).
105 //
106 static void
107 enter_server_no_thread_entry (void)
108 {
109  db_on_server++;
110  er_stack_push_if_exists ();
111 
112  if (private_heap_id == 0)
113  {
114  assert (db_on_server == 1);
115  private_heap_id = db_create_private_heap ();
116  }
117 }
118 
119 //
120 // enter_server () - start simulating server mode
121 //
122 // return : pointer to thread entry
123 //
124 static THREAD_ENTRY *
125 enter_server ()
126 {
127  enter_server_no_thread_entry ();
128  return thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
129 }
130 
131 //
132 // exit_server_no_thread_entry () - exit server mode without getting a thread entry (e.g. when "starting" server).
133 //
134 static void
135 exit_server_no_thread_entry (void)
136 {
137  if ((db_on_server - 1) == 0 && private_heap_id != 0)
138  {
139  db_clear_private_heap (NULL, private_heap_id);
140  }
141  er_restore_last_error ();
142  db_on_server--;
143 }
144 
145 //
146 // exit_server () - exit server mode simulation
147 //
148 // thread_ref (in) : reference to thread entry used to enter server mode
149 //
150 static void
151 exit_server (const THREAD_ENTRY & thread_ref)
152 {
153  (void) thread_ref; // not really used; just to force caller declare obtain thread entry
154 
155  exit_server_no_thread_entry ();
156 }
157 #endif // SA_MODE
158 
159 #if defined(CS_MODE)
160 /*
161  * pack_const_string -
162  *
163  * return:
164  *
165  * buffer(in):
166  * cstring(in):
167  *
168  * NOTE:
169  */
170 static char *
171 pack_const_string (char *buffer, const char *cstring)
172 {
173  return or_pack_string (buffer, cstring);
174 }
175 
176 /*
177  * pack_string_with_null_padding - pack stream and add null.
178  * so stream is made as null terminated string.
179  *
180  * return:
181  *
182  * buffer(in):
183  * stream(in):
184  * len(in):
185  *
186  * NOTE:
187  */
188 static char *
189 pack_string_with_null_padding (char *buffer, const char *stream, int len)
190 {
191  return or_pack_string_with_null_padding (buffer, stream, len);
192 }
193 
194 /*
195  * pack_const_string_with_length -
196  *
197  * return:
198  *
199  * buffer(in):
200  * cstring(in):
201  * strlen(in):
202  *
203  * NOTE:
204  */
205 static char *
206 pack_const_string_with_length (char *buffer, const char *cstring, int strlen)
207 {
208  return or_pack_string_with_length (buffer, cstring, strlen);
209 }
210 
211 /*
212  * length_const_string -
213  *
214  * return:
215  *
216  * cstring(in):
217  * strlen(out): strlen(cstring)
218  */
219 static int
220 length_const_string (const char *cstring, int *strlen)
221 {
222  return or_packed_string_length (cstring, strlen);
223 }
224 
225 
226 /*
227  * length_string_with_null_padding - calculate length with null padding
228  *
229  * return:
230  *
231  * len(in): stream length
232  */
233 static int
234 length_string_with_null_padding (int len)
235 {
236  return or_packed_stream_length (len + 1); /* 1 for NULL padding */
237 }

240 /*
241  * locator_fetch -
242  *
243  * return:
244  *
245  * oidp(in):
246  * chn(in):
247  * lock(in):
248  * fetch_type(in): fetch version type
249  * class_oid(in):
250  * class_chn(in):
251  * prefetch(in):
252  * fetch_copyarea(in):
253  */
254 int
255 locator_fetch (OID * oidp, int chn, LOCK lock, LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE fetch_version_type, OID * class_oid, int class_chn,
256  int prefetch, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea)
257 {
258 #if defined(CS_MODE)
259  int success = ER_FAILED;
260  int req_error;
261  char *ptr;
262  OR_ALIGNED_BUF ((OR_OID_SIZE * 2) + (OR_INT_SIZE * 5)) a_request;
263  char *request;
264  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
265  char *reply;
266 
267  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
268  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
269 
270  assert (oidp->volid >= 0 && oidp->pageid >= 0 && oidp->slotid >= 0);
271 
272  ptr = or_pack_oid (request, oidp);
273  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, chn);
274  ptr = or_pack_lock (ptr, lock);
275  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) fetch_version_type);
276  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
277  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, class_chn);
278  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, prefetch);
279  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
280 
281  req_error =
282  net_client_request_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FETCH, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
283  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), fetch_copyarea);
284  if (!req_error)
285  {
286  ptr = reply + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
287  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
288  }
289  else
290  {
291  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
292  }
293 
294  return success;
295 #else /* CS_MODE */
296  int success = ER_FAILED;
297 
298  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
299 
300  success =
301  xlocator_fetch (thread_p, oidp, chn, lock, fetch_version_type, fetch_version_type, class_oid, class_chn, prefetch,
302  fetch_copyarea);
303 
304  exit_server (*thread_p);
305 
306  return success;
307 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
308 }
309 
310 /*
311  * locator_get_class -
312  *
313  * return:
314  *
315  * class_oid(in):
316  * class_chn(in):
317  * oid(in):
318  * lock(in):
319  * prefetching(in):
320  * fetch_copyarea(in):
321  *
322  * NOTE:
323  */
324 int
325 locator_get_class (OID * class_oid, int class_chn, const OID * oid, LOCK lock, int prefetching,
326  LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea)
327 {
328 #if defined(CS_MODE)
329  int req_error;
330  char *ptr;
331  int return_value = ER_FAILED;
332  OR_ALIGNED_BUF ((OR_OID_SIZE * 2) + (OR_INT_SIZE * 3)) a_request;
333  char *request;
334  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_OID_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
335  char *reply;
336 
337  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
338  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
339 
340  ptr = or_pack_oid (request, class_oid);
341  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, class_chn);
342  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, (OID *) oid);
343  ptr = or_pack_lock (ptr, lock);
344  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, prefetching);
345  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
346 
347  req_error =
348  net_client_request_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_GET_CLASS, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
349  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), fetch_copyarea);
350  if (!req_error)
351  {
352  ptr = reply + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
353  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
354  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &return_value);
355  }
356  else
357  {
358  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
359  }
360 
361  return return_value;
362 #else /* CS_MODE */
363  int success = ER_FAILED;
364 
365  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
366 
367  success = xlocator_get_class (thread_p, class_oid, class_chn, oid, lock, prefetching, fetch_copyarea);
368 
369  exit_server (*thread_p);
370 
371  return success;
372 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
373 }

375 /*
376  * locator_fetch_all -
377  *
378  * return:
379  *
380  * hfid(in):
381  * lock(in):
382  * fetch_version_type(in): fetch version type
383  * class_oidp(in):
384  * nobjects(in):
385  * nfetched(in):
386  * last_oidp(in):
387  * fetch_copyarea(in):
388  *
389  * NOTE:
390  */
391 int
392 locator_fetch_all (const HFID * hfid, LOCK * lock, LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE fetch_version_type, OID * class_oidp,
393  int *nobjects, int *nfetched, OID * last_oidp, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea)
394 {
395 #if defined(CS_MODE)
396  int req_error;
397  char *ptr;
398  int return_value = ER_FAILED;
399  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_HFID_SIZE + (OR_INT_SIZE * 4) + (OR_OID_SIZE * 2)) a_request;
400  char *request;
401  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + (OR_INT_SIZE * 4) + OR_OID_SIZE) a_reply;
402  char *reply;
403 
404  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
405  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
406 
407  ptr = or_pack_hfid (request, hfid);
408  ptr = or_pack_lock (ptr, *lock);
409  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, fetch_version_type);
410  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oidp);
411  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, *nobjects);
412  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, *nfetched);
413  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, last_oidp);
414  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
415 
416  req_error =
417  net_client_request_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FETCHALL, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
418  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), fetch_copyarea);
419  if (req_error == NO_ERROR)
420  {
421  ptr = reply + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
422  ptr = or_unpack_lock (ptr, lock);
423  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, nobjects);
424  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, nfetched);
425  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, last_oidp);
426  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &return_value);
427  }
428  else
429  {
430  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
431  }
432 
433  return return_value;
434 #else /* CS_MODE */
435  int success = ER_FAILED;
436 
437  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
438 
439  success =
440  xlocator_fetch_all (thread_p, hfid, lock, fetch_version_type, class_oidp, nobjects, nfetched, last_oidp,
441  fetch_copyarea);
442 
443  exit_server (*thread_p);
444 
445  return success;
446 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
447 }
448 
449 /*
450  * locator_does_exist -
451  *
452  * return:
453  *
454  * oidp(in):
455  * chn(in):
456  * lock(in):
457  * class_oid(in):
458  * class_chn(in):
459  * need_fetching(in):
460  * prefetch(in):
461  * fetch_copyarea(in):
462  *
463  * NOTE:
464  */
465 int
466 locator_does_exist (OID * oidp, int chn, LOCK lock, OID * class_oid, int class_chn, int need_fetching, int prefetch,
467  LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea, LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE fetch_version_type)
468 {
469 #if defined(CS_MODE)
470  int does_exist = LC_ERROR;
471  int req_error;
472  char *ptr;
473  OR_ALIGNED_BUF ((OR_OID_SIZE * 2) + (OR_INT_SIZE * 6)) a_request;
474  char *request;
475  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_OID_SIZE) a_reply;
476  char *reply;
477  OID class_;
478 
479  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
480  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
481 
482  ptr = or_pack_oid (request, oidp);
483  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, chn);
484  ptr = or_pack_lock (ptr, lock);
485  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) fetch_version_type);
486  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
487  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, class_chn);
488  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, need_fetching);
489  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, prefetch);
490 
491  if (fetch_copyarea != NULL && need_fetching)
492  {
493  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
494  }
495 
496  req_error =
497  net_client_request_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_DOESEXIST, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
498  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), fetch_copyarea);
499  if (!req_error)
500  {
501  ptr = reply + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
502  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &does_exist);
503  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, &class_);
504  if (does_exist == LC_EXIST && class_oid)
505  {
506  COPY_OID (class_oid, &class_);
507  }
508  }
509  else if (fetch_copyarea != NULL)
510  {
511  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
512  }
513 
514  return does_exist;
515 #else /* CS_MODE */
516  int success = ER_FAILED;
517 
518  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
519 
520  success =
521  xlocator_does_exist (thread_p, oidp, chn, lock, fetch_version_type, class_oid, class_chn, need_fetching, prefetch,
522  fetch_copyarea);
523 
524  exit_server (*thread_p);
525 
526  return success;
527 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
528 }

530 /*
531  * locator_notify_isolation_incons -
532  *
533  * return:
534  *
535  * synch_copyarea(in):
536  *
537  * NOTE:
538  */
539 int
540 locator_notify_isolation_incons (LC_COPYAREA ** synch_copyarea)
541 {
542 #if defined(CS_MODE)
543  int success = ER_FAILED;
544  int req_error;
545  char *ptr;
546  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
547  char *reply;
548 
549  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
550 
551  *synch_copyarea = NULL;
552  req_error =
553  net_client_request_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_NOTIFY_ISOLATION_INCONS, NULL, 0, reply,
554  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), synch_copyarea);
555 
556  if (!req_error)
557  {
558  ptr = reply + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
559  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
560  }
561  else
562  {
563  *synch_copyarea = NULL;
564  }
565 
566  return (success);
567 #else /* CS_MODE */
568  int success = ER_FAILED;
569 
570  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
571 
572  success = xlocator_notify_isolation_incons (thread_p, synch_copyarea);
573 
574  exit_server (*thread_p);
575 
576  return success;
577 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
578 }

580 /*
581  * locator_repl_force - flush copy area containing replication objects and receive error occurred in server
582  *
583  * return:
584  *
585  * copy_area(in):
586  * reply_copy_area(out):
587  *
588  * NOTE:
589  */
590 int
591 locator_repl_force (LC_COPYAREA * copy_area, LC_COPYAREA ** reply_copy_area)
592 {
593 #if defined(CS_MODE)
594  int error_code = ER_FAILED;
595  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE) a_request;
596  char *request;
597  char *request_ptr;
598  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
599  char *reply;
600  char *desc_ptr = NULL;
601  int desc_size;
602  char *content_ptr;
603  int content_size;
604  int num_objs = 0;
605  int req_error;
606 
607  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
608  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
609 
610  num_objs = locator_send_copy_area (copy_area, &content_ptr, &content_size, &desc_ptr, &desc_size);
611 
612  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request, num_objs);
613  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, desc_size);
614  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, content_size);
615 
616  req_error =
617  net_client_request_3_data_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_REPL_FORCE, request, NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE, desc_ptr,
618  desc_size, content_ptr, content_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
619  reply_copy_area);
620 
621  if (req_error == NO_ERROR)
622  {
623  /* skip first 3 */
624  (void) or_unpack_int (reply + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE, &error_code);
625  }
626  else
627  {
628  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
629  error_code = er_errid ();
630  }
631 
632  if (desc_ptr)
633  {
634  free_and_init (desc_ptr);
635  }
636 
637  return error_code;
638 #else /* CS_MODE */
639  /* Not allowed in SA_MODE */
640  return ER_FAILED;
641 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
642 }
643 
644 /*
645  * locator_force -
646  *
647  * return:
648  *
649  * copy_area(in):
650  *
651  * NOTE:
652  */
653 int
654 locator_force (LC_COPYAREA * copy_area, int num_ignore_error_list, int *ignore_error_list, int content_size)
655 {
656 #if defined(CS_MODE)
657  int error_code = ER_FAILED;
658  char *request;
659  char *request_ptr;
660  int request_size;
661  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 3) a_reply;
662  char *reply;
663  char *desc_ptr = NULL;
664  int desc_size;
665  char *content_ptr;
666  int num_objs = 0;
667  int req_error;
668  int i;
669  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs;
670 
671  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (copy_area);
672 
673  request_size = OR_INT_SIZE * (6 + num_ignore_error_list);
674  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
675 
676  if (request == NULL)
677  {
678  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
679  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
680  }
681 
682  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
683 
684  num_objs = locator_send_copy_area (copy_area, &content_ptr, NULL, &desc_ptr, &desc_size);
685 
686  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request, num_objs);
687  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, mobjs->start_multi_update);
688  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, mobjs->end_multi_update);
689  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, desc_size);
690  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, content_size);
691 
692  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, num_ignore_error_list);
693  for (i = 0; i < num_ignore_error_list; i++)
694  {
695  request_ptr = or_pack_int (request_ptr, ignore_error_list[i]);
696  }
697 
698  req_error =
699  net_client_request_3_data (NET_SERVER_LC_FORCE, request, request_size, desc_ptr, desc_size, content_ptr,
700  content_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), desc_ptr, desc_size, NULL, 0);
701  if (!req_error)
702  {
703  (void) or_unpack_int (reply, &error_code);
704  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
705  {
706  locator_unpack_copy_area_descriptor (num_objs, copy_area, desc_ptr);
707  }
708  }
709  if (desc_ptr)
710  {
711  free_and_init (desc_ptr);
712  }
713  if (request)
714  {
715  free_and_init (request);
716  }
717 
718  return error_code;
719 #else /* CS_MODE */
720  int error_code = ER_FAILED;
721  LC_COPYAREA *copy_area_clone;
722 
723  /* If xlocator_force returns error, the original copy_area should not be changed. So copy_area_clone will be used. */
724  copy_area_clone = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (copy_area->length);
725  if (copy_area_clone == NULL)
726  {
727  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
728  }
729 
730  memcpy (copy_area_clone->mem, copy_area->mem, copy_area->length);
731 
732  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
733 
734  error_code = xlocator_force (thread_p, copy_area, num_ignore_error_list, ignore_error_list);
735 
736  exit_server (*thread_p);
737 
738  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
739  {
740  /* Restore copy_area */
741  memcpy (copy_area->mem, copy_area_clone->mem, copy_area->length);
742  }
743 
744  locator_free_copy_area (copy_area_clone);
745 
746  return error_code;
747 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
748 }
749 
750 /*
751  * locator_fetch_lockset -
752  *
753  * return:
754  *
755  * lockset(in):
756  * fetch_copyarea(in):
757  *
758  * NOTE:
759  */
760 int
761 locator_fetch_lockset (LC_LOCKSET * lockset, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea)
762 {
763 #if defined(CS_MODE)
764  int success = ER_FAILED;
765  int req_error;
766  char *ptr;
767  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
768  char *reply;
769  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
770  char *request;
771  static int eid;
772  char *packed = NULL;
773  int packed_size;
774  int send_size;
775 
776  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
777  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
778 
779  if (lockset->first_fetch_lockset_call == true)
780  {
781  send_size = locator_pack_lockset (lockset, true, true);
782 
783  packed = lockset->packed;
784  packed_size = lockset->packed_size;
785 
786  if (!packed)
787  {
788  return ER_FAILED;
789  }
790 
791  ptr = or_pack_int (request, send_size);
792 
793  req_error =
794  net_client_request_2recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FETCH_LOCKSET, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
795  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), packed, send_size, packed, packed_size,
796  fetch_copyarea, &eid);
797  }
798  else
799  {
800  /* Don't need to send the lockset information any more */
801  packed = lockset->packed;
802  packed_size = lockset->packed_size;
803  req_error =
804  net_client_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FETCH_LOCKSET, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), packed,
805  packed_size, fetch_copyarea, eid);
806  }
807 
808  if (!req_error)
809  {
810  ptr = reply + NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
811  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
812  if (success == NO_ERROR)
813  {
814  locator_unpack_lockset (lockset, lockset->first_fetch_lockset_call, false);
815  }
816  }
817  else
818  {
819  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
820  }
821 
822  /*
823  * We will not need to send the lockset structure any more. We do not
824  * need to receive the classes and objects in the lockset structure
825  * any longer
826  */
827  lockset->first_fetch_lockset_call = false;
828 
829  return success;
830 #else /* CS_MODE */
831  int success = ER_FAILED;
832 
833  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
834 
835  success = xlocator_fetch_lockset (thread_p, lockset, fetch_copyarea);
836 
837  exit_server (*thread_p);
838 
839  return success;
840 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
841 }
842 
843 /*
844  * locator_fetch_all_reference_lockset -
845  *
846  * return:
847  *
848  * oid(in):
849  * chn(in):
850  * class_oid(in):
851  * class_chn(in):
852  * lock(in):
853  * quit_on_errors(in):
854  * prune_level(in):
855  * lockset(in):
856  * fetch_copyarea(in):
857  *
858  * NOTE:
859  */
860 int
861 locator_fetch_all_reference_lockset (OID * oid, int chn, OID * class_oid, int class_chn, LOCK lock, int quit_on_errors,
862  int prune_level, LC_LOCKSET ** lockset, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea)
863 {
864 #if defined(CS_MODE)
865  int success = ER_FAILED;
866  int req_error;
867  char *ptr;
868  OR_ALIGNED_BUF ((OR_OID_SIZE * 2) + (OR_INT_SIZE * 5)) a_request;
869  char *request;
870  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
871  char *reply;
872  char *packed;
873  int packed_size;
874 
875  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
876  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
877 
878  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
879  *lockset = NULL;
880 
881  ptr = or_pack_oid (request, oid);
882  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, chn);
883  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
884  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, class_chn);
885  ptr = or_pack_lock (ptr, lock);
886  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, quit_on_errors);
887  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, prune_level);
888 
889  req_error =
890  net_client_request_3recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FETCH_ALLREFS_LOCKSET, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request),
891  reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &packed, &packed_size,
892  fetch_copyarea);
893 
894  if (!req_error)
895  {
896  ptr = reply + NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
897  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
898  if (packed_size > 0 && packed != NULL)
899  {
900  *lockset = locator_allocate_and_unpack_lockset (packed, packed_size, true, true, false);
901  }
902  else
903  {
904  *lockset = NULL;
905  }
906 
907  if (packed)
908  {
909  free_and_init (packed);
910  }
911  }
912  else
913  {
914  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
915  *lockset = NULL;
916  }
917 
918  return success;
919 
920 #else /* CS_MODE */
921  int success = ER_FAILED;
922 
923  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
924 
925  success =
926  xlocator_fetch_all_reference_lockset (thread_p, oid, chn, class_oid, class_chn, lock, quit_on_errors, prune_level,
927  lockset, fetch_copyarea);
928 
929  exit_server (*thread_p);
930 
931  return success;
932 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
933 }

935 /*
936  * locator_find_class_oid -
937  *
938  * return:
939  *
940  * class_name(in):
941  * class_oid(in):
942  * lock(in):
943  *
944  * NOTE:
945  */
946 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
947 locator_find_class_oid (const char *class_name, OID * class_oid, LOCK lock)
948 {
949 #if defined(CS_MODE)
950  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME found = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
951  int xfound;
952  int req_error;
953  char *ptr;
954  int request_size, strlen;
955  char *request;
956  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_OID_SIZE) a_reply;
957  char *reply;
958 
959  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
960 
961  request_size = length_const_string (class_name, &strlen) + OR_OID_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE;
962  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
963  if (request == NULL)
964  {
965  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
966  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
967  }
968 
969  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (request, class_name, strlen);
970  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
971  ptr = or_pack_lock (ptr, lock);
972 
973  req_error = net_client_request (NET_SERVER_LC_FIND_CLASSOID, request, request_size, reply,
974  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
975  if (!req_error)
976  {
977  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &xfound);
978  found = (LC_FIND_CLASSNAME) xfound;
979  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
980  }
981  free_and_init (request);
982 
983  return found;
984 #else /* CS_MODE */
985  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME found = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
986 
987  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
988 
989  found = xlocator_find_class_oid (thread_p, class_name, class_oid, lock);
990 
991  exit_server (*thread_p);
992 
993  return found;
994 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
995 }

997 /*
998  * locator_reserve_class_names -
999  *
1000  * return:
1001  *
1002  * num_classes(in)
1003  * class_names(in):
1004  * class_oids(in):
1005  *
1006  * NOTE:
1007  */
1008 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
1009 locator_reserve_class_names (const int num_classes, const char **class_names, OID * class_oids)
1010 {
1011 #if defined(CS_MODE)
1012  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME reserved = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1013  int xreserved;
1014  int request_size;
1015  int req_error;
1016  char *request, *ptr;
1017  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
1018  char *reply;
1019  int i;
1020 
1021  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
1022 
1023  request_size = OR_INT_SIZE;
1024  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; ++i)
1025  {
1026  request_size += length_const_string (class_names[i], NULL) + OR_OID_SIZE;
1027  }
1028  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
1029  if (request == NULL)
1030  {
1031  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
1032  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1033  }
1034 
1035  ptr = or_pack_int (request, num_classes);
1036  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; ++i)
1037  {
1038  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, class_names[i]);
1039  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, &class_oids[i]);
1040  }
1041 
1042  req_error = net_client_request (NET_SERVER_LC_RESERVE_CLASSNAME, request, request_size, reply,
1043  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
1044  if (!req_error)
1045  {
1046  (void) or_unpack_int (reply, &xreserved);
1047  reserved = (LC_FIND_CLASSNAME) xreserved;
1048  }
1049 
1050  free_and_init (request);
1051 
1052  return reserved;
1053 #else /* CS_MODE */
1054  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME reserved = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1055 
1056  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
1057 
1058  reserved = xlocator_reserve_class_names (thread_p, num_classes, class_names, class_oids);
1059 
1060  exit_server (*thread_p);
1061 
1062  return reserved;
1063 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
1064 }

1096  }

1099

1101  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
1102  free_and_init (request);
1103 
1104  if (request_error != NO_ERROR)
1105  {
1106  return request_error;
1107  }
1108 
1109  (void) or_unpack_oid (reply, class_oid);
1110 
1111  return NO_ERROR;
1112 #else
1113  int is_reserved;

1120

1122 #endif
1123 }

1240 /*
1241  * locator_assign_oid -
1242  *
1243  * return:
1244  *
1245  * hfid(in):
1246  * perm_oid(in):
1247  * expected_length(in):
1248  * class_oid(in):
1249  * class_name(in):
1250  *
1251  * NOTE:
1252  */
1253 int
1254 locator_assign_oid (const HFID * hfid, OID * perm_oid, int expected_length, OID * class_oid, const char *class_name)
1255 {

1265

1267  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
1268  if (request == NULL)
1269  {
1270  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
1271  return ER_FAILED;
1272  }

1276  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oid);

1278 
1279  req_error = net_client_request (NET_SERVER_LC_ASSIGN_OID, request, request_size, reply,
1280  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
1281  if (!req_error)
1282  {
1283  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &success);
1284  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, perm_oid);
1285  }
1286  free_and_init (request);
1287 
1288  return success;
1289 #else /* CS_MODE */

1299 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
1300 }

1302 /*
1303  * locator_assign_oid_batch -
1304  *
1305  * return:
1306  *
1307  * oidset(in):
1308  *
1309  * NOTE:
1310  */
1311 int
1312 locator_assign_oid_batch (LC_OIDSET * oidset)
1313 {
1314 #if defined(CS_MODE)
1315  int success = ER_FAILED;
1316  int packed_size;
1317  char *buffer, *ptr;
1318  int req_error;
1319 
1320  /*
1321  * Build a buffer in which to send and receive the goobers. We'll
1322  * reuse the same buffer to receive the data as we used to send it.
1323  * First word is reserved for the return code.
1324  */
1325  packed_size = locator_get_packed_oid_set_size (oidset) + OR_INT_SIZE;
1326  buffer = (char *) malloc (packed_size);
1327  if (buffer == NULL)
1328  {
1329  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) packed_size);
1330  return ER_FAILED;
1331  }
1332 
1333  ptr = buffer;
1334  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, 0);
1335 
1336  if (locator_pack_oid_set (ptr, oidset) == NULL)
1337  {
1338  free_and_init (buffer);
1339  return ER_FAILED;
1340  }
1341 
1342  req_error =
1343  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_LC_ASSIGN_OID_BATCH, buffer, packed_size, buffer, packed_size, NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
1344 
1345  if (!req_error)
1346  {
1347  ptr = buffer;
1348  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
1349  if (success == NO_ERROR)
1350  {
1351  if (locator_unpack_oid_set_to_exist (ptr, oidset) == false)
1352  {
1353  success = ER_FAILED;
1354  }
1355  }
1356  }
1357 
1358  free_and_init (buffer);
1359 
1360  return success;
1361 #else /* CS_MODE */
1362  int success = ER_FAILED;
1363 
1364  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
1365 
1366  success = xlocator_assign_oid_batch (thread_p, oidset);
1367 
1368  exit_server (*thread_p);
1369 
1370  return (success);
1371 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
1372 }
1373 
1374 /*
1375  * locator_find_lockhint_class_oids -
1376  *
1377  * return:
1378  *
1379  * num_classes(in):
1380  * many_classnames(in):
1381  * many_locks(in):
1382  * many_need_subclasses(in):
1383  * many_flags(in):
1384  * guessed_class_oids(in):
1385  * guessed_class_chns(in):
1386  * quit_on_errors(in):
1387  * lock_rr_tran(in):
1388  * lockhint(in):
1389  * fetch_copyarea(in):
1390  *
1391  * NOTE:
1392  */
1393 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
1394 locator_find_lockhint_class_oids (int num_classes, const char **many_classnames, LOCK * many_locks,
1395  int *many_need_subclasses, LC_PREFETCH_FLAGS * many_flags, OID * guessed_class_oids,
1396  int *guessed_class_chns, int quit_on_errors, LOCK lock_rr_tran,
1397  LC_LOCKHINT ** lockhint, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea)
1398 {
1399 #if defined(CS_MODE)
1400  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME allfind = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1401  int xallfind;
1402  int req_error;
1403  char *ptr;
1404  int request_size;
1405  char *request, *packed;
1406  int packed_size;
1407  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
1408  char *reply;
1409  int i;
1410 
1411  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
1412 
1413  *lockhint = NULL;
1414  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
1415 
1416  request_size = OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE;
1417  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
1418  {
1419  request_size += (length_const_string (many_classnames[i], NULL) + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE
1420  + OR_OID_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE);
1421  }
1422 
1423  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
1424  if (request == NULL)
1425  {
1426  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
1427  return allfind;
1428  }
1429 
1430  ptr = or_pack_int (request, num_classes);
1431  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, quit_on_errors);
1432  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) lock_rr_tran);
1433  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
1434  {
1435  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, many_classnames[i]);
1436  ptr = or_pack_lock (ptr, many_locks[i]);
1437  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, many_need_subclasses[i]);
1438  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) many_flags[i]);
1439  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, &guessed_class_oids[i]);
1440  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, guessed_class_chns[i]);
1441  }
1442 
1443  req_error =
1444  net_client_request_3recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FIND_LOCKHINT_CLASSOIDS, request, request_size, reply,
1445  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &packed, &packed_size, fetch_copyarea);
1446 
1447  if (!req_error)
1448  {
1449  ptr = reply + NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
1450  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &xallfind);
1451  allfind = (LC_FIND_CLASSNAME) xallfind;
1452 
1453  if (packed_size > 0 && packed != NULL)
1454  {
1455  *lockhint = locator_allocate_and_unpack_lockhint (packed, packed_size, true, false);
1456  }
1457  else
1458  {
1459  *lockhint = NULL;
1460  }
1461 
1462  if (packed)
1463  {
1464  free_and_init (packed);
1465  }
1466  }
1467  else
1468  {
1469  *lockhint = NULL;
1470  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
1471  }
1472 
1473  if (request != NULL)
1474  {
1475  free_and_init (request);
1476  }
1477 
1478  tm_Tran_rep_read_lock = lock_rr_tran;
1479 
1480  return allfind;
1481 #else /* CS_MODE */
1482  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME allfind = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1483 
1484  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
1485 
1486  allfind =
1487  xlocator_find_lockhint_class_oids (thread_p, num_classes, many_classnames, many_locks, many_need_subclasses,
1488  many_flags, guessed_class_oids, guessed_class_chns, quit_on_errors, lockhint,
1489  fetch_copyarea);
1490 
1491  exit_server (*thread_p);
1492 
1493  return allfind;
1494 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
1495 }
1496 
1497 /*
1498  * locator_fetch_lockhint_classes -
1499  *
1500  * return:
1501  *
1502  * lockhint(in):
1503  * fetch_copyarea(in):
1504  *
1505  * NOTE:
1506  */
1507 int
1508 locator_fetch_lockhint_classes (LC_LOCKHINT * lockhint, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_copyarea)
1509 {
1510 #if defined(CS_MODE)
1511  static int eid; /* TODO: remove static */
1512  int success = ER_FAILED;
1513  int req_error;
1514  char *ptr;
1515  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
1516  char *reply;
1517  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
1518  char *request;
1519  char *packed = NULL;
1520  int packed_size;
1521  int send_size;
1522 
1523  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
1524  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
1525 
1526  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
1527 
1528  if (lockhint->first_fetch_lockhint_call == true)
1529  {
1530  send_size = locator_pack_lockhint (lockhint, true);
1531 
1532  packed = lockhint->packed;
1533  packed_size = lockhint->packed_size;
1534 
1535  if (!packed)
1536  {
1537  return ER_FAILED;
1538  }
1539 
1540  ptr = or_pack_int (request, send_size);
1541 
1542  req_error =
1543  net_client_request_2recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FETCH_LOCKHINT_CLASSES, request,
1544  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
1545  packed, send_size, packed, packed_size, fetch_copyarea, &eid);
1546  }
1547  else
1548  {
1549  /* Don't need to send the lockhint information any more */
1550  packed = lockhint->packed;
1551  packed_size = lockhint->packed_size;
1552  req_error =
1553  net_client_recv_copyarea (NET_SERVER_LC_FETCH_LOCKHINT_CLASSES, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), packed,
1554  packed_size, fetch_copyarea, eid);
1555  }
1556 
1557  if (!req_error)
1558  {
1559  ptr = reply + NET_SENDRECV_BUFFSIZE + NET_COPY_AREA_SENDRECV_SIZE;
1560  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
1561  if (success == NO_ERROR)
1562  {
1563  locator_unpack_lockhint (lockhint, lockhint->first_fetch_lockhint_call);
1564  }
1565  }
1566  else
1567  {
1568  *fetch_copyarea = NULL;
1569  }
1570 
1571  lockhint->first_fetch_lockhint_call = false;
1572 
1573  return success;
1574 
1575 #else /* CS_MODE */
1576  int success = ER_FAILED;
1577 
1578  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
1579 
1580  success = xlocator_fetch_lockhint_classes (thread_p, lockhint, fetch_copyarea);
1581 
1582  exit_server (*thread_p);
1583 
1584  return success;
1585 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
1586 }

1588 /*
1589  * heap_create -
1590  *
1591  * return:
1592  *
1593  * hfid(in):
1594  * class_oid(in):
1595  * reuse_oid(in):
1596  *
1597  * NOTE:
1598  */
1599 int
1600 heap_create (HFID * hfid, const OID * class_oid, bool reuse_oid)
1601 {
1602 #if defined(CS_MODE)
1603  int error = ER_NET_CLIENT_DATA_RECEIVE;
1604  int req_error;
1605  char *ptr;
1606  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_HFID_SIZE + OR_OID_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
1607  char *request;
1608  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_HFID_SIZE) a_reply;
1609  char *reply;
1610 
1611  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
1612  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
1613 
1614  ptr = or_pack_hfid (request, hfid);
1615  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, (OID *) class_oid);
1616  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) reuse_oid);
1617  req_error =
1618  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_HEAP_CREATE, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
1619  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
1620  if (!req_error)
1621  {
1622  ptr = or_unpack_errcode (reply, &error);
1623  ptr = or_unpack_hfid (ptr, hfid);
1624  }
1625 
1626  return error;
1627 #else /* CS_MODE */
1628  int success;
1629 
1630  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
1631 
1632  success = xheap_create (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, reuse_oid);
1633 
1634  exit_server (*thread_p);
1635 
1636  return success;
1637 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
1638 }

1997 /*
1998  * log_reset_wait_msecs -
1999  *
2000  * return:
2001  *
2002  * wait_msecs(in): in milliseconds
2003  *
2004  * NOTE:
2005  */
2006 int
2007 log_reset_wait_msecs (int wait_msecs)
2008 {
2009 #if defined(CS_MODE)
2010  int wait = -1;
2011  int req_error;
2012  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
2013  char *request;
2014  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
2015  char *reply;
2016 
2017  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
2018  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
2019 
2020  (void) or_pack_int (request, wait_msecs);
2021 
2022  req_error =
2023  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_LOG_RESET_WAIT_MSECS, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
2024  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
2025  if (!req_error)
2026  {
2027  (void) or_unpack_int (reply, &wait);
2028  }
2029 
2030  return wait;
2031 #else /* CS_MODE */
2032  int wait = -1;
2033

2443 /*
2444  * tran_server_commit -
2445  *
2446  * return:
2447  *
2448  * retain_lock(in):
2449  *
2450  * NOTE:
2451  */
2452 TRAN_STATE
2453 tran_server_commit (bool retain_lock)
2454 {
2455 #if defined(CS_MODE)
2456  TRAN_STATE tran_state = TRAN_UNACTIVE_UNKNOWN;
2457  int req_error, tran_state_int, should_conn_reset;
2458  int i = 0;
2459  char *ptr;
2460  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE /* retain_lock */
2461  + OR_INT_SIZE /* row_count */
2462  + OR_INT_SIZE /* count of end query requests */
2463  + OR_PTR_SIZE * NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX /* query ids */
2464  + MAX_ALIGNMENT /* aligmnent */
2465  )a_request;
2466  char *request;
2467  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
2468  char *reply;
2469  int row_count = 0;
2470 
2471  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
2472  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
2473 
2474  /* Pack retain_lock */
2475  ptr = or_pack_int (request, (int) retain_lock);
2476  /* Pack row_count */
2477  row_count = db_get_row_count_cache ();
2478  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, row_count);
2479  /* Pack query ids to end */
2480  assert (net_Deferred_end_queries_count <= NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX);
2481  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, net_Deferred_end_queries_count);
2482  for (i = 0; i < net_Deferred_end_queries_count; i++)
2483  {
2484  ptr = or_pack_ptr (ptr, net_Deferred_end_queries[i]);
2485  }
2486  net_Deferred_end_queries_count = 0;
2487  assert (CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - request) <= (int) OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request));
2488 
2489  req_error =
2490  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_TM_SERVER_COMMIT, request, CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - request), reply,
2491  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
2492  if (!req_error)
2493  {
2494  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &tran_state_int);
2495  tran_state = (TRAN_STATE) tran_state_int;
2496  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &should_conn_reset);
2497  if (should_conn_reset != 0 && log_does_allow_replication ())
2498  {
2499  /*
2500  * fail-back action
2501  * make the client to reconnect to the active server
2502  */
2503  db_Connect_status = DB_CONNECTION_STATUS_RESET;
2504  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "tran_server_commit: DB_CONNECTION_STATUS_RESET\n");
2505  }
2506  }
2507 
2508  net_cleanup_client_queues ();
2509 
2510  return tran_state;
2511 #else /* CS_MODE */
2512  TRAN_STATE tran_state = TRAN_UNACTIVE_UNKNOWN;
2513 
2514  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
2515 
2516  tran_state = xtran_server_commit (thread_p, retain_lock);
2517 
2518  exit_server (*thread_p);
2519 
2520  return tran_state;
2521 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
2522 }

2532 tran_server_abort (void)

2600  return "(KILLED)";

3449 #if defined(CS_MODE)
3450 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)

3453  int req_error;

3462  + length_const_string (client_credential->db_name, NULL) /* db_name */
3463  + length_const_string (client_credential->db_user, NULL) /* db_user */
3464  + length_const_string (client_credential->db_password, NULL) /* db_password */

3466  + length_const_string (client_credential->login_name, NULL) /* login_name */

3471  + OR_INT_SIZE /* db_npages */
3472  + OR_INT_SIZE /* db_desired_log_page_size */
3473  + OR_INT_SIZE /* log_npages */
3474  + length_const_string (db_path_info->db_path, NULL) /* db_path */
3475  + length_const_string (db_path_info->vol_path, NULL) /* vol_path */
3476  + length_const_string (db_path_info->log_path, NULL) /* log_path */
3477  + length_const_string (db_path_info->db_host, NULL) /* db_host */
3478  + length_const_string (db_path_info->db_comments, NULL) /* db_comments */
3479  + length_const_string (file_addmore_vols, NULL) /* file_addmore_vols */
3480  + OR_INT_SIZE /* client_lock_wait */
3481  + OR_INT_SIZE /* client_isolation */ );
3482 
3483  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
3484  if (request)
3485  {
3486  ptr = or_pack_int (request, client_credential->client_type);
3487  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->client_info);
3488  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->db_name);
3489  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->db_user);

3497  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, db_npages);
3498  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, db_desired_log_page_size);
3499  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, log_npages);
3500  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, db_path_info->db_path);
3501  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, db_path_info->vol_path);
3502  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, db_path_info->log_path);

3508

3510  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_BO_INIT_SERVER, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
3511  NULL, 0, NULL, 0);

3513  {
3514  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &tran_index);
3515  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, rootclass_oid);
3516  ptr = or_unpack_hfid (ptr, rootclass_hfid);
3517  }
3518  free_and_init (request);
3519  }
3520  else
3521  {

3523  }
3524 
3525  return tran_index;
3526 #else /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
3527  /* Should not called in CS_MODE */
3528  assert (0);

3530 #endif /* !ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
3531 #else /* CS_MODE */

3533

3538  db_desired_pagesize, log_npages, db_desired_log_page_size, rootclass_oid, rootclass_hfid,

3547 /*
3548  * boot_register_client -
3549  *
3550  * return:
3551  *
3552  * client_credential(in)

3555  * tran_state(out):
3556  * server_credential(out):

3558 int
3559 boot_register_client (BOOT_CLIENT_CREDENTIAL * client_credential, int client_lock_wait, TRAN_ISOLATION client_isolation,
3560  TRAN_STATE * tran_state, BOOT_SERVER_CREDENTIAL * server_credential)
3561 {
3562 #if defined(CS_MODE)
3563  int tran_index = NULL_TRAN_INDEX;
3564  int request_size, area_size, req_error, temp_int;
3565  char *request, *reply, *area, *ptr;
3566  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;

3569 
3570  request_size = (OR_INT_SIZE /* client_type */
3571  + length_const_string (client_credential->client_info, NULL) /* client_info */
3572  + length_const_string (client_credential->db_name, NULL) /* db_name */
3573  + length_const_string (client_credential->db_user, NULL) /* db_user */
3574  + length_const_string (client_credential->db_password, NULL) /* db_password */
3575  + length_const_string (client_credential->program_name, NULL) /* prog_name */
3576  + length_const_string (client_credential->login_name, NULL) /* login_name */
3577  + length_const_string (client_credential->host_name, NULL) /* host_name */
3578  + OR_INT_SIZE /* process_id */
3579  + OR_INT_SIZE /* client_lock_wait */
3580  + OR_INT_SIZE /* client_isolation */ );
3581

3583  if (request == NULL)
3584  {

3586  return NULL_TRAN_INDEX;

3590  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->client_info);
3591  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->db_name);
3592  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->db_user);
3593  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->db_password);

3595  ptr = pack_const_string (ptr, client_credential->login_name);

3597  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, client_credential->process_id);
3598  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, client_lock_wait);
3599  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) client_isolation);
3600

3602  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &area, &area_size);
3603  if (!req_error)
3604  {
3605  or_unpack_int (reply, &area_size);
3606  if (area_size > 0)
3607  {
3608  int ha_state_to_int;
3609 
3610  ptr = or_unpack_int (area, &tran_index);
3611 
3612  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &temp_int);
3613  *tran_state = (TRAN_STATE) temp_int;
3614 
3615  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &server_credential->db_full_name);
3616  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &server_credential->host_name);
3617  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &server_credential->lob_path);
3618  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &server_credential->process_id);
3619  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, &server_credential->root_class_oid);
3620  ptr = or_unpack_hfid (ptr, &server_credential->root_class_hfid);
3621 
3622  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &temp_int);
3623  server_credential->page_size = (PGLENGTH) temp_int;
3624 
3625  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &temp_int);
3626  server_credential->log_page_size = (PGLENGTH) temp_int;
3627 
3628  ptr = or_unpack_float (ptr, &server_credential->disk_compatibility);
3629 
3630  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &ha_state_to_int);
3631  server_credential->ha_server_state = (HA_SERVER_STATE) ha_state_to_int;
3632 
3633  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &server_credential->db_charset);
3634  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &server_credential->db_lang);
3635  }

3640 
3641  return tran_index;

3644

3648  xboot_register_client (NULL, client_credential, client_lock_wait, client_isolation, tran_state, server_credential);
3649  exit_server_no_thread_entry ();

3655 /*
3656  * boot_unregister_client -
3657  *
3658  * return:
3659  *
3660  * tran_index(in):
3661  *
3662  * NOTE:
3663  */
3664 int
3665 boot_unregister_client (int tran_index)
3666 {
3667 #if defined(CS_MODE)
3668  int error_code = ER_FAILED;
3669  int req_error;
3670  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
3671  char *request;
3672  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
3673  char *reply;
3674 
3675  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
3676  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
3677 
3678  (void) or_pack_int (request, tran_index);
3679 
3680  req_error = net_client_request (NET_SERVER_BO_UNREGISTER_CLIENT, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
3681  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
3682  if (req_error == NO_ERROR)
3683  {
3684  or_unpack_int (reply, &error_code);
3685  }
3686  else
3687  {
3688  error_code = req_error;
3689  }
3690 
3691  return error_code;
3692 #else /* CS_MODE */
3693  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
3694 
3695  if (!BO_IS_SERVER_RESTARTED ())
3696  {
3697  // server is killed already
3698  return NO_ERROR;
3699  }
3700 
3701  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
3702 
3703  error_code = xboot_unregister_client (thread_p, tran_index);
3704  if (tran_index == NULL_TRAN_INDEX)
3705  {
3706  assert (thread_p == NULL);
3707  exit_server_no_thread_entry ();
3708  }
3709  else
3710  {
3711  exit_server (*thread_p);
3712  }
3713 
3714  return error_code;
3715 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
3716 }

3718 /*
3719  * boot_backup -
3720  *
3721  * return:
3722  *
3723  * backup_path(in):
3724  * backup_level(in):
3725  * delete_unneeded_logarchives(in):
3726  * backup_verbose_file(in):
3727  * num_threads(in):
3728  * zip_method(in):
3729  * zip_level(in):
3730  * skip_activelog(in):
3731  * sleep_msecs(in):
3732  *
3733  * NOTE:
3734  */
3735 int
3736 boot_backup (const char *backup_path, FILEIO_BACKUP_LEVEL backup_level, bool delete_unneeded_logarchives,
3737  const char *backup_verbose_file, int num_threads, FILEIO_ZIP_METHOD zip_method, FILEIO_ZIP_LEVEL zip_level,
3738  int skip_activelog, int sleep_msecs)
3739 {
3740 #if defined(CS_MODE)
3741  int success = ER_FAILED;
3742  int request_size, strlen1, strlen2;
3743  char *request, *ptr;
3744  int req_error;
3745  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 3) a_reply;
3746  char *reply;
3747  char *rd1, *rd2;
3748  int d1, d2;
3749  int cb_type;
3750 
3751  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
3752 
3753  request_size = (length_const_string (backup_path, &strlen1) + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE
3754  + length_const_string (backup_verbose_file, &strlen2) + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE
3755  + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE);
3756 
3757  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
3758  if (request == NULL)
3759  {
3760  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
3761  return ER_FAILED;
3762  }
3763 
3764  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (request, backup_path, strlen1);
3765  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, backup_level);
3766  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, delete_unneeded_logarchives ? 1 : 0);
3767  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, backup_verbose_file, strlen2);
3768  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, num_threads);
3769  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, zip_method);
3770  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, zip_level);
3771  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, skip_activelog);
3772  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, sleep_msecs);
3773  req_error =
3774  net_client_request_with_callback (NET_SERVER_BO_BACKUP, request, request_size, reply,
3775  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0, &rd1, &d1, &rd2, &d2, NULL,
3776  NULL);
3777  if (!req_error)
3778  {
3779  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &cb_type);
3780  or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
3781  /* we just ignore the last part of the reply */
3782  }
3783  free_and_init (request);
3784 
3785  return success;
3786 #else /* CS_MODE */
3787  int success = false;
3788 
3789  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
3790 
3791  success = xboot_backup (thread_p, backup_path, backup_level, delete_unneeded_logarchives, backup_verbose_file,
3792  num_threads, zip_method, zip_level, skip_activelog, sleep_msecs);
3793 
3794  exit_server (*thread_p);
3795 
3796  return success;
3797 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
3798 }

3865 /*
3866  * boot_check_db_consistency -
3867  *
3868  * return:
3869  *
3870  * check_flag(in):
3871  *
3872  * NOTE:
3873  */
3874 int
3875 boot_check_db_consistency (int check_flag, OID * oids, int num_oids, BTID * index_btid)
3876 {
3877 #if defined(CS_MODE)
3878  int success = ER_FAILED;
3879  int req_error;
3880  int cb_type;
3881  char *rd1, *rd2;
3882  int d1, d2;
3883  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 3) a_reply;
3884  char *reply;
3885  char *request, *ptr;
3886  size_t request_size;
3887  int i;
3888 
3889  request_size = OR_INT_SIZE; /* check_flag */
3890  request_size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* num_oid */
3891  request_size += (OR_OID_SIZE * num_oids);
3892  request_size += OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE;
3893 
3894  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
3895  if (request == NULL)
3896  {
3897  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
3898  return ER_FAILED;
3899  }
3900 
3901  ptr = or_pack_int (request, check_flag);
3902  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, num_oids);
3903  for (i = 0; i < num_oids; i++)
3904  {
3905  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, &oids[i]);
3906  }
3907  ptr = or_pack_btid (ptr, index_btid);
3908 
3909  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
3910  req_error = net_client_request_with_callback (NET_SERVER_BO_CHECK_DBCONSISTENCY, request, (int) request_size, reply,
3911  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0, &rd1, &d1, &rd2, &d2,
3912  NULL, NULL);
3913  free_and_init (request);
3914 
3915  if (!req_error)
3916  {
3917  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &cb_type);
3918  or_unpack_int (ptr, &success);
3919  }
3920 
3921  return success;
3922 #else /* CS_MODE */
3923  int success = ER_FAILED;
3924 
3925  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
3926 
3927  success = xboot_check_db_consistency (thread_p, check_flag, oids, num_oids, index_btid);
3928 
3929  exit_server (*thread_p);

4170 /*
4171  * csession_find_or_create_session - check if session is still active
4172  * if not, create a new session
4173  *
4174  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
4175  * session_id (in/out) : the id of the session to end
4176  * row_count (out) : the value of row count for this session
4177  * server_session_key (in/out) :
4178  */
4179 int
4180 csession_find_or_create_session (SESSION_ID * session_id, int *row_count, char *server_session_key, const char *db_user,
4181  const char *host, const char *program_name)
4182 {
4183 #if defined (CS_MODE)
4184  int req_error;
4185  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
4186  char *reply = NULL;
4187  char *request = NULL, *area = NULL;
4188  char *ptr;
4189  int request_size, area_size;
4190  int db_user_len, host_len, program_name_len;
4191  SESSION_PARAM *session_params = NULL;
4192  int error = NO_ERROR, update_parameter_values = 0;
4193 
4194  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
4195  request_size = OR_INT_SIZE; /* session_id */
4196  request_size += or_packed_stream_length (SERVER_SESSION_KEY_SIZE);
4197  request_size += sysprm_packed_session_parameters_length (cached_session_parameters, request_size);
4198  request_size += length_const_string (db_user, &db_user_len);
4199  request_size += length_const_string (host, &host_len);
4200  request_size += length_const_string (program_name, &program_name_len);
4201 
4202  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
4203 
4204  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
4205  if (request == NULL)
4206  {
4207  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
4208  return ER_FAILED;
4209  }
4210 
4211  ptr = or_pack_int (request, ((int) *session_id));
4212  ptr = or_pack_stream (ptr, server_session_key, SERVER_SESSION_KEY_SIZE);
4213  ptr = sysprm_pack_session_parameters (ptr, cached_session_parameters);
4214  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, db_user, db_user_len);
4215  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, host, host_len);
4216  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, program_name, program_name_len);
4217 
4218  req_error =
4219  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_SES_CHECK_SESSION, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
4220  NULL, 0, &area, &area_size);
4221 
4222  if (req_error == NO_ERROR)
4223  {
4224  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &area_size);
4225  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &error);
4226  if (error != NO_ERROR)
4227  {
4228  free_and_init (request);
4229  return error;
4230  }
4231 
4232  if (area_size > 0)
4233  {
4234  ptr = or_unpack_int (area, (int *) session_id);
4235  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, row_count);
4236  ptr = or_unpack_stream (ptr, server_session_key, SERVER_SESSION_KEY_SIZE);
4237  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_parameter_values);
4238  if (update_parameter_values)
4239  {
4240  ptr = sysprm_unpack_session_parameters (ptr, &session_params);
4241  }
4242 
4243  free_and_init (area);
4244  }
4245  if (update_parameter_values)
4246  {
4247  /* session parameters were found in session state and must update parameter values */
4248  if (session_params == NULL)
4249  {
4250  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4251  error = er_errid ();
4252  if (error == NO_ERROR)
4253  {
4254  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
4255  error = ER_FAILED;
4256  }
4257  free_and_init (request);
4258  return error;
4259  }
4260  sysprm_update_client_session_parameters (session_params);
4261  }
4262  else
4263  {
4264  /* use the values stored in cached_session_parameters */
4265  sysprm_update_client_session_parameters (cached_session_parameters);
4266  }
4267  sysprm_free_session_parameters (&session_params);
4268  }
4269  free_and_init (request);
4270 
4271  return NO_ERROR;
4272 #else
4273  int result = NO_ERROR;
4274  SESSION_ID id;
4275 
4276  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
4277 
4278  if (db_Session_id == DB_EMPTY_SESSION)
4279  {
4280  result = xsession_create_new (thread_p, &id);
4281  }
4282  else
4283  {
4284  id = db_Session_id;
4285  if (xsession_check_session (thread_p, id) != NO_ERROR)
4286  {
4287  /* create new session */
4288  if (xsession_create_new (thread_p, &id) != NO_ERROR)
4289  {
4290  result = ER_FAILED;
4291  }
4292  }
4293  }
4294 
4295  db_Session_id = id;
4296  *session_id = db_Session_id;
4297 
4298  /* get row count */
4299  if (result != ER_FAILED)
4300  {
4301  xsession_get_row_count (thread_p, row_count);
4302  }
4303 
4304  exit_server (*thread_p);
4305 
4306  return result;
4307 #endif
4308 }
4309

4446 /*
4447  * csession_get_last_insert_id - get the value of the last update serial
4448  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
4449  * value (out) : the value of the last insert id
4450  * update_last_insert_id(in): whether update the last insert id
4451  */
4452 int
4453 csession_get_last_insert_id (DB_VALUE * value, bool update_last_insert_id)
4454 {
4455 #if defined (CS_MODE)
4456  int req_error;
4457  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
4458  char *reply;
4459  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
4460  char *request;
4461  char *ptr = NULL;
4462  char *data_reply = NULL;
4463  int data_size = 0;
4464 
4465  db_make_null (value);
4466 
4467  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
4468 
4469  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
4470  ptr = or_pack_int (request, update_last_insert_id);
4471

4473  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_SES_GET_LAST_INSERT_ID, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
4474  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &data_reply, &data_size);
4475  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
4476  {
4477  db_make_null (value);
4478  req_error = ER_FAILED;
4479  goto cleanup;
4480  }
4481 
4482  /* data_size */
4483  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &req_error);
4484  /* req_error */
4485  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &req_error);
4486  if (req_error != NO_ERROR || data_size == 0)
4487  {
4488  req_error = (req_error != NO_ERROR) ? req_error : ER_FAILED;
4489  goto cleanup;
4490  }
4491 
4492  or_unpack_value (data_reply, value);
4493 
4494 cleanup:
4495  if (data_reply != NULL)
4496  {
4497  free_and_init (data_reply);
4498  }
4499 
4500  return req_error;
4501 #else
4502  int result = NO_ERROR;
4503  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
4504 
4505  result = xsession_get_last_insert_id (thread_p, value, update_last_insert_id);
4506 
4507  exit_server (*thread_p);
4508 
4509  return result;
4510 #endif
4511 }

4550 /*
4551  * csession_create_prepared_statement () - create a prepared session statement
4552  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
4553  * name (in) : the name of the prepared statement
4554  * alias_print(in): the compiled statement string
4555  * stmt_info (in) : serialized prepared statement information
4556  * info_length(in): the size of the serialized buffer
4557  */
4558 int
4559 csession_create_prepared_statement (const char *name, const char *alias_print, char *stmt_info, int info_length)
4560 {
4561 #if defined (CS_MODE)
4562  int req_error;
4563  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
4564  char *request = NULL;
4565  char *reply = NULL;
4566  char *ptr = NULL;
4567  int req_size = 0, name_len = 0, alias_print_len = 0;
4568  SHA1Hash alias_sha1 = SHA1_HASH_INITIALIZER;
4569 
4570  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
4571 
4572  req_size = 0;
4573  /* packed size for name */
4574  req_size += length_const_string (name, &name_len);
4575  /* packed size for alias_print */
4576  req_size += length_const_string (alias_print, &alias_print_len);
4577  /* data_size */
4578  req_size += OR_INT_SIZE;
4579  if (alias_print != NULL)
4580  {
4581  /* sha1 */
4582  req_size += OR_SHA1_SIZE;
4583  }
4584 
4585  request = (char *) malloc (req_size);
4586  if (request == NULL)
4587  {
4588  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) req_size);
4589  req_error = ER_FAILED;
4590  goto cleanup;
4591  }
4592 
4593  /* name */
4594  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (request, name, name_len);
4595  /* alias_print */
4596  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, alias_print, alias_print_len);
4597  /* data size */
4598  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, info_length);
4599 
4600  if (alias_print)
4601  {
4602  req_error = SHA1Compute ((const unsigned char *) alias_print, (unsigned) strlen (alias_print), &alias_sha1);
4603  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
4604  {
4605  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4606  goto cleanup;
4607  }
4608  ptr = or_pack_sha1 (ptr, &alias_sha1);
4609  }
4610 
4611  req_error =
4612  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_SES_CREATE_PREPARED_STATEMENT, request, req_size, reply,
4613  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), stmt_info, info_length, NULL, 0);
4614  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
4615  {
4616  goto cleanup;
4617  }
4618  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &req_error);
4619 
4620 cleanup:
4621  if (request != NULL)
4622  {
4623  free_and_init (request);
4624  }
4625  return req_error;
4626 #else
4627  int result = NO_ERROR;
4628  char *local_name = NULL;
4629  char *local_alias_print = NULL;
4630  char *local_stmt_info = NULL;
4631  size_t len = 0;
4632  SHA1Hash alias_sha1 = SHA1_HASH_INITIALIZER;
4633 
4634  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
4635 
4636  /* The server keeps a packed version of the prepared statement information and we need to pack it here */
4637 
4638  /* copy name */
4639  if (name != NULL)
4640  {
4641  len = strlen (name);
4642  local_name = (char *) malloc (len + 1);
4643  if (local_name == NULL)
4644  {
4645  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, len + 1);
4646  result = ER_FAILED;
4647  goto error;
4648  }
4649  memcpy (local_name, name, len);
4650  local_name[len] = 0;
4651  }
4652 
4653  /* copy alias print */
4654  if (alias_print != NULL)
4655  {
4656  len = strlen (alias_print);
4657  local_alias_print = (char *) malloc (len + 1);
4658  if (local_alias_print == NULL)
4659  {
4660  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, len + 1);
4661  result = ER_FAILED;
4662  goto error;
4663  }
4664  memcpy (local_alias_print, alias_print, len);
4665  local_alias_print[len] = 0;
4666 
4667  result = SHA1Compute ((const unsigned char *) alias_print, (unsigned) strlen (alias_print), &alias_sha1);
4668  if (result != NO_ERROR)
4669  {
4670  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4671  return result;
4672  }
4673  }
4674 
4675  /* copy stmt_info */
4676  if (stmt_info != NULL)
4677  {
4678  local_stmt_info = (char *) malloc (info_length);
4679  if (local_stmt_info == NULL)
4680  {
4681  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) info_length);
4682  result = ER_FAILED;
4683  goto error;
4684  }
4685  memcpy (local_stmt_info, stmt_info, info_length);
4686  }
4687 
4688  result =
4689  xsession_create_prepared_statement (thread_p, local_name, local_alias_print, &alias_sha1, local_stmt_info,
4690  info_length);
4691  if (result != NO_ERROR)
4692  {
4693  goto error;
4694  }
4695 
4696  exit_server (*thread_p);
4697 
4698  return result;
4699 
4700 error:
4701 
4702  if (local_name != NULL)
4703  {
4704  free_and_init (local_name);
4705  }
4706  if (local_alias_print != NULL)
4707  {
4708  free_and_init (local_alias_print);
4709  }
4710  if (local_stmt_info != NULL)
4711  {
4712  free_and_init (local_stmt_info);
4713  }
4714 
4715  exit_server (*thread_p);
4716 
4717  return result;
4718 #endif
4719 }

4721 /*
4722  * csession_get_prepared_statement () - get information about a prepared session statement
4723  * return : error code or no error
4724  * name (in) : the name of the prepared statement
4725  * xasl_id (out) : XASL id
4726  * stmt_info (out) : serialized prepared statement information
4727  * xasl_header_p (out) : if pointer is not null, request XASL node header along with XASL_ID.
4728  */
4729 int
4730 csession_get_prepared_statement (const char *name, XASL_ID * xasl_id, char **stmt_info,
4731  XASL_NODE_HEADER * xasl_header_p)
4732 {
4733 #if defined (CS_MODE)
4734  int req_error = NO_ERROR;
4735  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2 + OR_XASL_ID_SIZE) a_reply;
4736  char *reply = NULL;
4737  char *reply_data = NULL;
4738  char *request = NULL;
4739  char *ptr = NULL;
4740  int req_size = 0, len = 0;
4741  int reply_size = 0;
4742  int get_xasl_header = xasl_header_p != NULL;
4743 
4744  INIT_XASL_NODE_HEADER (xasl_header_p);
4745 
4746  req_size = (or_packed_string_length (name, &len) /* name */
4747  + OR_INT_SIZE /* get_xasl_header */ );
4748  request = (char *) malloc (req_size);
4749  if (request == NULL)
4750  {
4751  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) req_size);
4752  req_error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
4753  goto error;
4754  }
4755 
4756  ptr = or_pack_string_with_length (request, name, len);
4757  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, get_xasl_header);
4758 
4759  req_error =
4760  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_SES_GET_PREPARED_STATEMENT, request, req_size, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply),
4761  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &reply_data, &reply_size);
4762  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
4763  {
4764  goto error;
4765  }
4766 
4767  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
4768  /* unpack reply_size */
4769  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &req_error);
4770  /* unpack error code */
4771  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &req_error);
4772  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
4773  {
4774  /* there was an error fetching session data */
4775  goto error;
4776  }
4777  OR_UNPACK_XASL_ID (ptr, xasl_id);
4778 
4779  ptr = or_unpack_string_alloc (reply_data, stmt_info);
4780  if (*stmt_info == NULL)
4781  {
4782  req_error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4783  goto error;
4784  }
4785  if (get_xasl_header)
4786  {
4787  OR_UNPACK_XASL_NODE_HEADER (ptr, xasl_header_p);
4788  }
4789 
4790  if (request != NULL)
4791  {
4792  free_and_init (request);
4793  }
4794  if (reply_data != NULL)
4795  {
4796  free_and_init (reply_data);
4797  }
4798  return req_error;
4799 
4800 error:
4801  if (request != NULL)
4802  {
4803  free_and_init (request);
4804  }
4805  if (reply_data != NULL)
4806  {
4807  free_and_init (reply_data);
4808  }
4809 
4810  return req_error;
4811 #else
4812  int result = NO_ERROR;
4813  int stmt_info_len = 0;
4814 
4815  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
4816 
4817  INIT_XASL_NODE_HEADER (xasl_header_p);
4818  result = xsession_get_prepared_statement (thread_p, name, stmt_info, &stmt_info_len, xasl_id, xasl_header_p);
4819 
4820  exit_server (*thread_p);
4821 
4822  return result;
4823 #endif
4824 }

4936  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
4937  * variables (in) : variables
4938  * count (in) : count
4939  */
4940 int
4941 csession_set_session_variables (DB_VALUE * variables, const int count)
4942 {

4944  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;

4951

4953  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
4954  {
4955  req_size += OR_VALUE_ALIGNED_SIZE (&variables[i]);
4956  }
4957

4959  if (data_request == NULL)
4960  {

4962  err = ER_FAILED;

4964  }

4968  {
4969  ptr = or_pack_db_value (ptr, &variables[i]);
4970  }

4974  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply), OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
4975  data_request, req_size, NULL, 0);
4976  if (err != NO_ERROR)
4977  {
4978  goto cleanup;
4979  }
4980 
4981  or_unpack_int (OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply), &err);
4982 
4983 cleanup:

4985  {
4986  free_and_init (data_request);
4987  }
4988 
4989  return err;
4990 #else
4991  int err = 0;
4992

4994 
4995  err = xsession_set_session_variables (thread_p, variables, count);
4996

4998 
4999  return err;
5000 #endif
5001 }

5072 /*
5073  * csession_get_variable () - get the value of a session variable
5074  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
5075  * name (in) : the name of the session variable
5076  * value (out) : the value of the session variable
5077  */
5078 int
5079 csession_get_variable (DB_VALUE * name, DB_VALUE * value)
5080 {
5081 #if defined (CS_MODE)
5082  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_reply;
5083  char *request = NULL, *reply = NULL, *ptr = NULL;
5084  int req_size = 0, err = NO_ERROR, reply_size = 0;
5085 
5086  assert (value != NULL);
5087 
5088  req_size = OR_VALUE_ALIGNED_SIZE (name);
5089 
5090  request = (char *) malloc (req_size);
5091  if (request == NULL)
5092  {
5093  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) req_size);
5094  return ER_FAILED;
5095  }
5096 
5097  or_pack_db_value (request, name);
5098 
5099  err =
5100  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_SES_GET_SESSION_VARIABLE, request, req_size, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply),
5101  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &reply, &reply_size);
5102  if (err != NO_ERROR)
5103  {
5104  goto cleanup;
5105  }
5106 
5107  /* a_reply contains reply_size code and error code */
5108  ptr = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
5109  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &err);
5110  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &err);
5111  if (err != NO_ERROR)
5112  {
5113  goto cleanup;
5114  }
5115 
5116  or_unpack_db_value (reply, value);
5117 
5118 cleanup:
5119  if (request != NULL)
5120  {
5121  free_and_init (request);
5122  }
5123  if (reply != NULL)
5124  {
5125  free_and_init (reply);
5126  }
5127 
5128  return err;
5129 #else
5130  int err = NO_ERROR;
5131  DB_VALUE *val_ref = NULL;
5132 
5133  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
5134  /* we cannot use the allocation methods from the server context so we will just get a reference here */
5135  err = xsession_get_session_variable_no_copy (thread_p, name, &val_ref);
5136 
5137  exit_server (*thread_p);
5138 
5139  if (err == NO_ERROR)
5140  {
5141  assert (val_ref != NULL);
5142  /* create a clone of this value to be used in the client scope */
5143  pr_clone_value (val_ref, value);
5144  }
5145  else
5146  {
5147  db_make_null (value);
5148  }
5149  return err;
5150 #endif
5151 }

5183 /*
5184  * boot_copy () - copy the database to a new destination
5185  *
5186  * return : NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
5187  *
5188  * fromdb_name(in): The database from where the copy is made.
5189  * newdb_name(in): Name of new database
5190  * newdb_path(in): Directory where the new database will reside
5191  * newlog_path(in): Directory where the log volumes of the new database will reside
5192  * new_lob_path(in): Directory where the lob volumes of the new database will reside
5193  * newdb_server_host(in): Server host where the new database reside
5194  * new_volext_path(in): A path is included if all volumes are placed in one place/directory. If NULL is given,
5195  * - If file "fileof_vols_and_wherepaths" is given, the path is found in this file.
5196  * - Each volume is copied to same place where the volume resides.
5197  * Note: This parameter should be NULL, if the above file is given.
5198  * fileof_vols_and_wherepaths(in): A file is given when the user decides to control the copy/rename of the volume by
5199  * individual bases. That is, user decides to spread the volumes over several locations and
5200  * or to label the volumes with specific names.
5201  * Each volume entry consists of: volid from_fullvolname to_fullvolname
5202  * newdb_overwrite(in): Whether to overwrite the new database if it already exist.
5203  */
5204 int
5205 boot_copy (const char *from_dbname, const char *new_db_name, const char *new_db_path, const char *new_log_path,
5206  const char *new_lob_path, const char *new_db_server_host,
5207  const char *new_volext_path, const char *fileof_vols_and_copypaths, bool new_db_overwrite)
5208 {
5209 #if defined(CS_MODE)
5210  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_ONLY_IN_STANDALONE, 1, "copy database");
5211  return ER_FAILED;
5212 #else /* CS_MODE */
5213  int error_code;
5214 
5215  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
5216 
5217  error_code =
5218  xboot_copy (thread_p, from_dbname, new_db_name, new_db_path, new_log_path, new_lob_path, new_db_server_host,
5219  new_volext_path, fileof_vols_and_copypaths, new_db_overwrite);
5220  assert (thread_p == NULL);
5221 
5222  exit_server_no_thread_entry ();
5223 
5224  return error_code;
5225 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
5226 }

5235 int
5236 boot_emergency_patch (const char *db_name, bool recreate_log, DKNPAGES log_npages, const char *db_locale, FILE * out_fp)
