5482 /*
5483  * btree_add_index () -
5484  *
5485  * return:
5486  *
5487  * btid(in):
5488  * key_type(in):
5489  * class_oid(in):
5490  * attr_id(in):
5491  * unique_pk(in):
5492  *
5493  * NOTE:
5494  */
5495 int
5496 btree_add_index (BTID * btid, TP_DOMAIN * key_type, OID * class_oid, int attr_id, int unique_pk)
5497 {
5498 #if defined(CS_MODE)
5499  int error = NO_ERROR;
5500  int req_error, request_size, domain_size;
5501  char *ptr;
5502  char *request;
5503  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE) a_reply;
5504  char *reply;
5505 
5506  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
5507 
5508  domain_size = or_packed_domain_size (key_type, 0);
5509  request_size = OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE + domain_size + OR_OID_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE;
5510 
5511  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
5512  if (request == NULL)
5513  {
5514  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
5515  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
5516  }
5517 
5518  ptr = or_pack_btid (request, btid);
5519  ptr = or_pack_domain (ptr, key_type, 0, 0);
5520  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
5521  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, attr_id);
5522  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, unique_pk);
5523 
5524  req_error =
5525  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_BTREE_ADDINDEX, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
5526  NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
5527  if (!req_error)
5528  {
5529  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &error);
5530  ptr = or_unpack_btid (ptr, btid);
5531  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5532  {
5533  btid = NULL;
5534  }
5535  }
5536 
5537  free_and_init (request);
5538 
5539  return error;
5540 #else /* CS_MODE */
5541  int error = NO_ERROR;
5542 
5543  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
5544 
5545  btid = xbtree_add_index (thread_p, btid, key_type, class_oid, attr_id, unique_pk, 0, 0, 0);
5546  if (btid == NULL)
5547  {
5548  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5549  error = er_errid ();
5550  }
5551 
5552  exit_server (*thread_p);
5553 
5554  return error;
5555 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
5556 }
5557 
5558 /*
5559  * btree_load_index -
5560  *
5561  * return:
5562  *
5563  * btid(in):
5564  * bt_name(in):
5565  * key_type(in):
5566  * class_oids(in):
5567  * n_classes(in):
5568  * n_attrs(in):
5569  * attr_ids(in):
5570  * hfids(in):
5571  * unique_pk(in):
5572  * fk_refcls_oid(in):
5573  * fk_refcls_pk_btid(in):
5574  * fk_name(in):
5575  *
5576  * NOTE:
5577  */
5578 int
5579 btree_load_index (BTID * btid, const char *bt_name, TP_DOMAIN * key_type, OID * class_oids, int n_classes, int n_attrs,
5580  int *attr_ids, int *attrs_prefix_length, HFID * hfids, int unique_pk, int not_null_flag,
5581  OID * fk_refcls_oid, BTID * fk_refcls_pk_btid, const char *fk_name, char *pred_stream,
5582  int pred_stream_size, char *expr_stream, int expr_stream_size, int func_col_id,
5583  int func_attr_index_start, SM_INDEX_STATUS index_status)
5584 {
5585 #if defined(CS_MODE)
5586  int error = NO_ERROR, req_error, request_size, domain_size;
5587  char *ptr;
5588  char *request;
5589  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE) a_reply;
5590  char *reply;
5591  int i, total_attrs, bt_strlen, fk_strlen;
5592  int index_info_size = 0;
5593  char *stream = NULL;
5594  int stream_size = 0;
5595 
5596  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
5597 
5598  if (pred_stream && expr_stream)
5599  {
5600  return ER_FAILED;
5601  }
5602 
5603  index_info_size = (OR_INT_SIZE /* index info type */
5604  + (pred_stream ? OR_INT_SIZE : 0) + (expr_stream ? OR_INT_SIZE * 3 : 0));
5605 
5606  domain_size = or_packed_domain_size (key_type, 0);
5607  request_size = (OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE /* BTID */
5608  + or_packed_string_length (bt_name, &bt_strlen) /* index name */
5609  + domain_size /* key_type */
5610  + (n_classes * OR_OID_SIZE) /* class_oids */
5611  + OR_INT_SIZE /* n_classes */
5612  + OR_INT_SIZE /* n_attrs */
5613  + (n_classes * n_attrs * OR_INT_SIZE) /* attr_ids */
5614  + ((n_classes == 1) ? (n_attrs * OR_INT_SIZE) : 0) /* attrs_prefix_length */
5615  + (n_classes * OR_HFID_SIZE) /* hfids */
5616  + OR_INT_SIZE /* unique_pk */
5617  + OR_INT_SIZE /* not_null_flag */
5618  + OR_OID_SIZE /* fk_refcls_oid */
5619  + OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE /* fk_refcls_pk_btid */
5620  + or_packed_string_length (fk_name, &fk_strlen) /* fk_name */
5621  + index_info_size /* filter predicate or function index stream size */
5622  + OR_INT_SIZE /* Index status */ );
5623 
5624  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
5625  if (request == NULL)
5626  {
5627  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
5628  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
5629  }
5630 
5631  ptr = or_pack_btid (request, btid);
5632  ptr = or_pack_string_with_length (ptr, bt_name, bt_strlen);
5633  ptr = or_pack_domain (ptr, key_type, 0, 0);
5634  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, n_classes);
5635  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, n_attrs);
5636 
5637  for (i = 0; i < n_classes; i++)
5638  {
5639  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, &class_oids[i]);
5640  }
5641 
5642  total_attrs = n_classes * n_attrs;
5643  for (i = 0; i < total_attrs; i++)
5644  {
5645  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, attr_ids[i]);
5646  }
5647 
5648  if (n_classes == 1)
5649  {
5650  for (i = 0; i < n_attrs; i++)
5651  {
5652  if (attrs_prefix_length)
5653  {
5654  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, attrs_prefix_length[i]);
5655  }
5656  else
5657  {
5658  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, -1);
5659  }
5660  }
5661  }
5662 
5663  for (i = 0; i < n_classes; i++)
5664  {
5665  ptr = or_pack_hfid (ptr, &hfids[i]);
5666  }
5667 
5668  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, unique_pk);
5669  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, not_null_flag);
5670 
5671  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, fk_refcls_oid);
5672  ptr = or_pack_btid (ptr, fk_refcls_pk_btid);
5673  ptr = or_pack_string_with_length (ptr, fk_name, fk_strlen);
5674 
5675  if (pred_stream)
5676  {
5677  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, 0);
5678  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, pred_stream_size);
5679  stream = pred_stream;
5680  stream_size = pred_stream_size;
5681  }
5682  else if (expr_stream)
5683  {
5684  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, 1);
5685  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, expr_stream_size);
5686  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, func_col_id);
5687  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, func_attr_index_start);
5688  stream = expr_stream;
5689  stream_size = expr_stream_size;
5690  }
5691  else
5692  {
5693  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, -1); /* stream=NULL, stream_size=0 */
5694  }
5695 
5696  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, index_status); /* Index status. */
5697 
5698  req_error =
5699  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_BTREE_LOADINDEX, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
5700  stream, stream_size, NULL, 0);
5701 
5702  if (!req_error)
5703  {
5704  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &error);
5705  ptr = or_unpack_btid (ptr, btid);
5706  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5707  {
5708  btid = NULL;
5709  }
5710  }
5711  else
5712  {
5713  btid = NULL;
5714  }
5715 
5716  free_and_init (request);
5717 
5718  return error;
5719 #else /* CS_MODE */
5720  int error = NO_ERROR;
5721 
5722  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
5723 
5724  btid =
5725  xbtree_load_index (thread_p, btid, bt_name, key_type, class_oids, n_classes, n_attrs, attr_ids, attrs_prefix_length,
5726  hfids, unique_pk, not_null_flag, fk_refcls_oid, fk_refcls_pk_btid, fk_name, pred_stream,
5727  pred_stream_size, expr_stream, expr_stream_size, func_col_id, func_attr_index_start);
5728  if (btid == NULL)
5729  {
5730  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5731  error = er_errid ();
5732  }
5733  else
5734  {
5735  error = NO_ERROR;
5736  }
5737 
5738  exit_server (*thread_p);
5739 
5740  return error;
5741 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
5742 }
5743

5865 /*
5866  * btree_find_unique -
5867  *
5868  * return:
5869  *
5870  * btid(in):
5871  * key(in):
5872  * class_oid(in):
5873  * oid(in):
5874  *
5875  * NOTE:
5876  */
5877 BTREE_SEARCH
5878 btree_find_unique (BTID * btid, DB_VALUE * key, OID * class_oid, OID * oid)
5879 {
5880 #if defined(CS_MODE)
5881  BTREE_SEARCH status = BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
5882  int req_error, request_size, key_size;
5883  char *ptr;
5884  char *request;
5885  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_OID_SIZE) a_reply;
5886  char *reply;
5887  enum net_server_request request_id;
5888 
5889  if (btid == NULL || key == NULL || class_oid == NULL || oid == NULL)
5890  {
5891  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
5892  return BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
5893  }
5894 
5895  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
5896 
5897  key_size = OR_VALUE_ALIGNED_SIZE (key);
5898  request_size = key_size + OR_OID_SIZE + OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE;
5899 
5900  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
5901  if (request == NULL)
5902  {
5903  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
5904  return BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
5905  }
5906 
5907  ptr = request;
5908  ptr = or_pack_value (ptr, key);
5909  request_id = NET_SERVER_BTREE_FIND_UNIQUE;
5910 
5911  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oid);
5912  ptr = or_pack_btid (ptr, btid);
5913 
5914  /* reset request_size as real packed size */
5915  request_size = CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - request);
5916 
5917  req_error =
5918  net_client_request (request_id, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
5919  if (!req_error)
5920  {
5921  int istatus;
5922  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &istatus);
5923  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, oid);
5924  status = (BTREE_SEARCH) istatus;
5925  }
5926  else
5927  {
5928  OID_SET_NULL (oid);
5929  }
5930 
5931  free_and_init (request);
5932  return status;
5933 
5934 #else /* CS_MODE */
5935  BTREE_SEARCH status = BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
5936 
5937  if (btid == NULL || key == NULL || class_oid == NULL || oid == NULL)
5938  {
5939  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
5940  return BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
5941  }
5942 
5943  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
5944  status = xbtree_find_unique (thread_p, btid, S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK, key, class_oid, oid, false);
5945  exit_server (*thread_p);
5946  return status;
5947 
5948 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
5949 }

5951 /*
5952  * btree_find_multi_uniques () - search a list of indexes of a specified class for a list of values
5953  * return: index search result or BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED
5954  * class_oid (in) : class OID
5955  * pruning_type (in) : pruning type
5956  * btids (in) : list of indexes to search
5957  * keys (in) : list of values to search for
5958  * count (in) : number of indexes
5959  * op_type (in) : operation type
5960  * oids (in/out) : found OIDs
5961  * oids_count (in/out) : number of OIDs found
5962  */
5963 BTREE_SEARCH
5964 btree_find_multi_uniques (OID * class_oid, int pruning_type, BTID * btids, DB_VALUE * keys, int count,
5965  SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE op_type, OID ** oids, int *oids_count)
5966 {
5967 #if defined (CS_MODE)
5968  int req_error, req_size, area_size, i;
5969  /* reply contains area size and return code */
5970  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (2 * OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
5971  char *request = NULL, *ptr = NULL;
5972  char *area = NULL;
5973  BTREE_SEARCH result = BTREE_KEY_NOTFOUND;
5974 
5975  /* compute request size */
5976  req_size = (OR_INT_SIZE /* number of indexes to search */
5977  + OR_INT_SIZE /* needs pruning */
5978  + OR_OID_SIZE /* class OID */
5979  + OR_INT_SIZE /* operation type */
5980  + (count * OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE) /* indexes */ );
5981 
5982  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
5983  {
5984  req_size += OR_VALUE_ALIGNED_SIZE (&keys[i]);
5985  }
5986 
5987  request = (char *) malloc (req_size);
5988  if (request == NULL)
5989  {
5990  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) req_size);
5991  result = BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
5992  goto cleanup;
5993  }
5994 
5995  /* pack oid */
5996  ptr = or_pack_oid (request, class_oid);
5997  /* needs pruning */
5998  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, pruning_type);
5999  /* operation type */
6000  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, op_type);
6001  /* number of indexes */
6002  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, count);
6003  /* indexes */
6004  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
6005  {
6006  ptr = or_pack_btid (ptr, &btids[i]);
6007  }
6008  /* values */
6009  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
6010  {
6011  ptr = or_pack_value (ptr, &keys[i]);
6012  }
6013 
6014  req_error =
6015  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_BTREE_FIND_MULTI_UNIQUES, request, req_size, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply),
6016  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &area, &area_size);
6017  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
6018  {
6019  result = BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
6020  goto cleanup;
6021  }
6022 
6023  /* skip over area_size */
6024  ptr = or_unpack_int (OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply), &area_size);
6025 
6026  /* unpack error code returned from server */
6027  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &req_error);
6028  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
6029  {
6030  result = BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
6031  goto cleanup;
6032  }
6033 
6034  /* if no data was returned, no offending OID was found */
6035  if (area_size == 0)
6036  {
6037  *oids = NULL;
6038  result = BTREE_KEY_NOTFOUND;
6039  goto cleanup;
6040  }
6041 
6042  /* unpack number of returned OIDs */
6043  ptr = or_unpack_int (area, oids_count);
6044  if (*oids_count == 0)
6045  {
6046  assert (false);
6047  *oids = NULL;
6048  result = BTREE_KEY_NOTFOUND;
6049  goto cleanup;
6050  }
6051  else
6052  {
6053  assert (*oids_count > 0);
6054  result = BTREE_KEY_FOUND;
6055  }
6056 
6057  *oids = (OID *) malloc ((*oids_count) * sizeof (OID));
6058  if (*oids == NULL)
6059  {
6060  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) req_size);
6061  result = BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
6062  goto cleanup;
6063  }
6064 
6065  for (i = 0; i < *oids_count; i++)
6066  {
6067  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, &((*oids)[i]));
6068  }
6069 
6070 cleanup:
6071  if (request != NULL)
6072  {
6073  free_and_init (request);
6074  }
6075  if (area != NULL)
6076  {
6077  free_and_init (area);
6078  }
6079  if (result != BTREE_KEY_FOUND)
6080  {
6081  *oids_count = 0;
6082  *oids = NULL;
6083  }
6084  return result;
6085 
6086 #else
6087  BTREE_SEARCH result = BTREE_KEY_NOTFOUND;
6088  OID *local_oids = NULL;
6089  int local_count = 0;
6090 
6091  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
6092 
6093  result =
6094  xbtree_find_multi_uniques (thread_p, class_oid, pruning_type, btids, keys, count, op_type, &local_oids,
6095  &local_count);
6096  if (result == BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED)
6097  {
6098  exit_server (*thread_p);
6099  return result;
6100  }
6101 
6102  /* need to copy memory from server context to local context */
6103  if (local_count > 0)
6104  {
6105  *oids = (OID *) malloc (local_count * sizeof (OID));
6106  if (*oids == NULL)
6107  {
6108  db_private_free (thread_p, local_oids);
6109  exit_server (*thread_p);
6110  return BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED;
6111  }
6112  *oids_count = local_count;
6113  memcpy (*oids, local_oids, local_count * sizeof (OID));
6114  db_private_free (thread_p, local_oids);
6115  }
6116 
6117  exit_server (*thread_p);
6118 
6119  return result;
6120 #endif
6121 }

6220 /*
6221  * qmgr_prepare_query - Send a SERVER_QM_PREPARE request to the server
6222  *
6223  * Send XASL stream and receive XASL file id (XASL_ID) as a result.
6224  * If xasl_buffer == NULL, the server will look up the XASL cache and then
6225  * return the cached XASL file id if found, otherwise return NULL.
6226  * This function is a counter part to sqmgr_prepare_query().
6227  *
6228  * return: Error Code.
6229  *
6230  * context(in): query string & plan
6231  * stream(in/out): xasl stream, size, xasl ID & xasl_header
6232  *
6233  * NOTE: If xasl_header_p is not null, also XASL node header will be requested
6234  */
6235 int
6236 qmgr_prepare_query (COMPILE_CONTEXT * context, XASL_STREAM * stream)
6237 {
6238 #if defined(CS_MODE)
6239  int error = NO_ERROR;
6240  int req_error, request_size = 0;
6241  int sql_hash_text_len, sql_plan_text_len, reply_buffer_size = 0;
6242  char *request = NULL, *reply = NULL, *ptr = NULL, *reply_buffer = NULL;
6243  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_XASL_ID_SIZE) a_reply;
6244  int get_xasl_header = stream->xasl_header != NULL;
6245 
6246  INIT_XASL_NODE_HEADER (stream->xasl_header);
6247 
6248  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
6249 
6250  /* sql hash text */
6251  request_size += length_const_string (context->sql_hash_text, &sql_hash_text_len);
6252 
6253  /* sql plan text */
6254  request_size += length_const_string (context->sql_plan_text, &sql_plan_text_len);
6255 
6256  /* sql user text */
6257  request_size += length_string_with_null_padding (context->sql_user_text_len);
6258 
6259  request_size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* size */
6260  request_size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* get_xasl_header */
6261  request_size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* whether to pin xasl cache entry */
6262  request_size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* whether to recompile the pinned xasl cache entry */
6263  request_size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* context->recompile_xasl */
6264  request_size += OR_SHA1_SIZE; /* sha1 */
6265 
6266  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
6267  if (request == NULL)
6268  {
6269  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
6270  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
6271  }
6272 
6273  /* pack query alias string as a request data */
6274  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (request, context->sql_hash_text, sql_hash_text_len);
6275  /* pack query plan as a request data */
6276  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, context->sql_plan_text, sql_plan_text_len);
6277  /* pack query string as a request data */
6278  ptr = pack_string_with_null_padding (ptr, context->sql_user_text, context->sql_user_text_len);
6279 
6280  /* pack size of XASL stream */
6281  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, stream->buffer_size);
6282  /* Pack get_xasl_header. */
6283  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, get_xasl_header);
6284  /* Pack context. */
6285  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) context->is_xasl_pinned_reference);
6286  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) context->recompile_xasl_pinned);
6287  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) context->recompile_xasl);
6288  ptr = or_pack_sha1 (ptr, &context->sha1);
6289 
6290  /* send SERVER_QM_QUERY_PREPARE request with request data and XASL stream; receive XASL file id (XASL_ID) as a reply */
6291  req_error =
6292  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_QM_QUERY_PREPARE, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
6293  (char *) stream->buffer, stream->buffer_size, &reply_buffer, &reply_buffer_size);
6294  if (!req_error)
6295  {
6296  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &reply_buffer_size);
6297  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &error);
6298  if (error == NO_ERROR)
6299  {
6300  /* NULL XASL_ID will be returned when cache not found */
6301  OR_UNPACK_XASL_ID (ptr, stream->xasl_id);
6302  context->recompile_xasl = false;
6303 
6304  if (reply_buffer != NULL && reply_buffer_size != 0)
6305  {
6306  ptr = reply_buffer;
6307  if (get_xasl_header)
6308  {
6309  OR_UNPACK_XASL_NODE_HEADER (ptr, stream->xasl_header);
6310  }
6311  if (ptr < reply_buffer + reply_buffer_size)
6312  {
6313  /* Doesn't really matter what it's packed... We need to force recompile; see sqmgr_prepare_query */
6314  assert ((ptr + OR_INT_SIZE) == (reply_buffer + reply_buffer_size));
6315  assert (!context->recompile_xasl);
6316  context->recompile_xasl = true;
6317  }
6318  }
6319  }
6320  else
6321  {
6322  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6323  }
6324  }
6325  else
6326  {
6327  error = req_error;
6328  }
6329 
6330  if (request != NULL)
6331  {
6332  free_and_init (request);
6333  }
6334 
6335  if (reply_buffer != NULL)
6336  {
6337  free_and_init (reply_buffer);
6338  }
6339 
6340  return error;
6341 #else /* CS_MODE */
6342  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6343  XASL_STREAM server_stream;
6344 
6345  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
6346 
6347  /* We cannot use the stream created on client context. XASL cache will save the stream in cache entry and it will
6348  * suppose the stream buffer was allocated using malloc.
6349  * Duplicate the stream for server context.
6350  */
6351  server_stream.xasl_id = stream->xasl_id;
6352  server_stream.xasl_header = stream->xasl_header;
6353  server_stream.buffer_size = stream->buffer_size;
6354  if (stream->buffer_size > 0)
6355  {
6356  server_stream.buffer = (char *) malloc (stream->buffer_size);
6357  if (server_stream.buffer == NULL)
6358  {
6359  exit_server (*thread_p);
6360 
6361  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, stream->buffer_size);
6362  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
6363  }
6364  memcpy (server_stream.buffer, stream->buffer, stream->buffer_size);
6365  }
6366  else
6367  {
6368  /* No stream. This is just a lookup for existing entry. */
6369  server_stream.buffer = NULL;
6370  }
6371 
6372  INIT_XASL_NODE_HEADER (server_stream.xasl_header);
6373 
6374  /* call the server routine of query prepare */
6375  error_code = xqmgr_prepare_query (thread_p, context, &server_stream);
6376  if (server_stream.buffer != NULL)
6377  {
6378  free_and_init (server_stream.buffer);
6379  }
6380  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6381  {
6382  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6383  }
6384 
6385  exit_server (*thread_p);
6386 
6387  return error_code;
6388 
6389 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
6390 }
6391 
6392 
6393 /*
6394  * qmgr_execute_query - Send a SERVER_QM_EXECUTE request to the server
6395  *
6396  * Send XASL file id and parameter values if exist and receive list file id
6397  * that contains query result. If an error occurs, return NULL QFILE_LIST_ID.
6398  * This function is a counter part to sqmgr_execute_query().
6399  */
6400 /*
6401  * qmgr_execute_query -
6402  *
6403  * return:
6404  *
6405  * xasl_id(in):
6406  * query_idp(in):
6407  * dbval_cnt(in):
6408  * dbvals(in):
6409  * flag(in):
6410  * clt_cache_time(in):
6411  * srv_cache_time(in):
6412  * query_timeout(in):
6413  * end_of_queries(in):
6414  *
6415  * NOTE:
6416  */
6417 QFILE_LIST_ID *
6418 qmgr_execute_query (const XASL_ID * xasl_id, QUERY_ID * query_idp, int dbval_cnt, const DB_VALUE * dbvals,
6419  QUERY_FLAG flag, CACHE_TIME * clt_cache_time, CACHE_TIME * srv_cache_time, int query_timeout)
6420 {
6421 #if defined(CS_MODE)
6422  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
6423  int req_error, senddata_size, replydata_size_listid, replydata_size_page, replydata_size_plan;
6424  char *request, *reply, *senddata = NULL;
6425  char *replydata_listid = NULL, *replydata_page = NULL, *replydata_plan = NULL, *ptr;
6426  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_XASL_ID_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE * 5 + OR_CACHE_TIME_SIZE
6427  + OR_PTR_SIZE * NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX + EXECUTE_QUERY_MAX_ARGUMENT_DATA_SIZE) a_request;
6428  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 7 + OR_PTR_ALIGNED_SIZE + OR_CACHE_TIME_SIZE) a_reply;
6429  int i, request_len;
6430  const DB_VALUE *dbval;
6431  CACHE_TIME local_srv_cache_time;
6432  int should_conn_reset, end_query_result, tran_state;
6433 
6434  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
6435  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
6436 
6437  /* make send data using if parameter values for host variables are given */
6438  senddata_size = 0;
6439  for (i = 0, dbval = dbvals; i < dbval_cnt; i++, dbval++)
6440  {
6441  senddata_size += OR_VALUE_ALIGNED_SIZE ((DB_VALUE *) dbval);
6442  }
6443  if (senddata_size != 0)
6444  {
6445  senddata = (char *) malloc (senddata_size);
6446  if (senddata == NULL)
6447  {
6448  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) senddata_size);
6449  return NULL;
6450  }
6451 
6452  ptr = senddata;
6453  for (i = 0, dbval = dbvals; i < dbval_cnt; i++, dbval++)
6454  {
6455  ptr = or_pack_db_value (ptr, (DB_VALUE *) dbval);
6456  }
6457 
6458  /* change senddata_size as real packing size */
6459  senddata_size = CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - senddata);
6460  if (senddata_size < EXECUTE_QUERY_MAX_ARGUMENT_DATA_SIZE)
6461  {
6462  flag |= EXECUTE_QUERY_WITHOUT_DATA_BUFFERS;
6463  }
6464  }
6465 
6466  /* pack XASL file id (XASL_ID), number of parameter values, size of the send data, and query execution mode flag as a
6467  * request data */
6468  ptr = request;
6469  OR_PACK_XASL_ID (ptr, xasl_id);
6470  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, dbval_cnt);
6471  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, senddata_size);
6472  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, flag);
6473  OR_PACK_CACHE_TIME (ptr, clt_cache_time);
6474  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, query_timeout);
6475 
6476  request_len = OR_XASL_ID_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE * 4 + OR_CACHE_TIME_SIZE;
6477  if (IS_QUERY_EXECUTE_WITH_COMMIT (flag))
6478  {
6479  assert (net_Deferred_end_queries_count <= NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX);
6480  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, net_Deferred_end_queries_count);
6481  for (i = 0; i < net_Deferred_end_queries_count; i++)
6482  {
6483  ptr = or_pack_ptr (ptr, net_Deferred_end_queries[i]);
6484  }
6485 
6486  request_len += OR_INT_SIZE + OR_PTR_SIZE * net_Deferred_end_queries_count;
6487  net_Deferred_end_queries_count = 0;
6488  }
6489 
6490  /* Add message in log in case of autocommit transactions. It helps to trace query execution. */
6491  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_ER_LOG_DEBUG) && IS_TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT (flag))
6492  {
6493  if (IS_QUERY_EXECUTE_WITH_COMMIT (flag))
6494  {
6495  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "qmgr_execute_query requested: EXECUTION_WITH_AUTOCOMMIT\n");
6496  }
6497  else
6498  {
6499  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "qmgr_execute_query requested: EXECUTION_WITHOUT_AUTOCOMMIT\n");
6500  }
6501  }
6502 
6503  if (IS_QUERY_EXECUTED_WITHOUT_DATA_BUFFERS (flag))
6504  {
6505  /* Execute without data buffers. The data has small size. Include the data in the argument buffer. */
6506  assert (senddata != NULL && 0 < senddata_size);
6507 
6508  memcpy (ptr, senddata, senddata_size);
6509  request_len += senddata_size;
6510 
6511  free_and_init (senddata);
6512  senddata_size = 0;
6513  }
6514  else
6515  {
6516  /* Execute with data buffer. The data has big size. */
6517  }
6518 
6519  req_error = net_client_request_with_callback (NET_SERVER_QM_QUERY_EXECUTE, request, request_len, reply,
6520  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), senddata, senddata_size, NULL, 0,
6521  &replydata_listid, &replydata_size_listid, &replydata_page,
6522  &replydata_size_page, &replydata_plan, &replydata_size_plan);
6523  if (replydata_plan != NULL)
6524  {
6525  db_set_execution_plan (replydata_plan, replydata_size_plan);
6526  free_and_init (replydata_plan);
6527  }
6528 
6529  if (senddata != NULL)
6530  {
6531  free_and_init (senddata);
6532  }
6533 
6534  if (!req_error)
6535  {
6536  /* first argument should be QUERY_END ptr = or_unpack_int(reply, &status); */
6537  /* second argument should be the same with replydata_size_listid ptr = or_unpack_int(ptr, &listid_length); */
6538  /* third argument should be the same with replydata_size_page ptr = or_unpack_int(ptr, &page_size); */
6539  /* third argument should be the same with replydata_size_plan ptr = or_unpack_int(ptr, &plan_size); */
6540  /* fourth argument should be query_id */
6541  ptr = or_unpack_ptr (reply + OR_INT_SIZE * 4, query_idp);
6542  OR_UNPACK_CACHE_TIME (ptr, &local_srv_cache_time);
6543  if (srv_cache_time)
6544  {
6545  memcpy (srv_cache_time, &local_srv_cache_time, sizeof (CACHE_TIME));
6546  }
6547 
6548  if (IS_QUERY_EXECUTE_WITH_COMMIT (flag))
6549  {
6550  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &end_query_result);
6551  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tran_state);
6552  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &should_conn_reset);
6553 
6554  if (tran_state == TRAN_UNACTIVE_COMMITTED || tran_state == TRAN_UNACTIVE_COMMITTED_INFORMING_PARTICIPANTS
6555  || tran_state == TRAN_UNACTIVE_ABORTED || tran_state == TRAN_UNACTIVE_ABORTED_INFORMING_PARTICIPANTS)
6556  {
6557  net_cleanup_client_queues ();
6558  }
6559 
6560  tran_set_latest_query_status (end_query_result, tran_state, should_conn_reset);
6561  }
6562 
6563  if (replydata_listid && replydata_size_listid)
6564  {
6565  /* unpack list file id of query result from the reply data */
6566  ptr = or_unpack_unbound_listid (replydata_listid, (void **) (&list_id));
6567  /* QFILE_LIST_ID shipped with last page */
6568  if (replydata_size_page)
6569  {
6570  list_id->last_pgptr = replydata_page;
6571  }
6572  else
6573  {
6574  list_id->last_pgptr = NULL;
6575  }
6576  free_and_init (replydata_listid);
6577  }
6578  }
6579 
6580  return list_id;
6581 #else /* CS_MODE */
6582  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
6583  DB_VALUE *server_db_values = NULL;
6584  OID *oid;
6585  int i;
6586 
6587  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
6588 
6589  /* reallocate dbvals to use server allocation */
6590  if (dbval_cnt > 0)
6591  {
6592  size_t s = dbval_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE);
6593 
6594  server_db_values = (DB_VALUE *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, s);
6595  if (server_db_values == NULL)
6596  {
6597  goto cleanup;
6598  }
6599  for (i = 0; i < dbval_cnt; i++)
6600  {
6601  db_make_null (&server_db_values[i]);
6602  }
6603  for (i = 0; i < dbval_cnt; i++)
6604  {
6605  switch (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&dbvals[i]))
6606  {
6607  case DB_TYPE_OBJECT:
6608  /* server cannot handle objects, convert to OID instead */
6609  oid = ws_identifier (db_get_object (&dbvals[i]));
6610  if (oid != NULL)
6611  {
6612  db_make_oid (&server_db_values[i], oid);
6613  }
6614  break;
6615 
6616  default:
6617  /* Clone value */
6618  if (db_value_clone ((DB_VALUE *) (&dbvals[i]), &server_db_values[i]) != NO_ERROR)
6619  {
6620  goto cleanup;
6621  }
6622  break;
6623  }
6624  }
6625  }
6626  else
6627  {
6628  /* No dbvals */
6629  server_db_values = NULL;
6630  }
6631 
6632  /* call the server routine of query execute */
6633  list_id =
6634  xqmgr_execute_query (thread_p, xasl_id, query_idp, dbval_cnt, server_db_values, &flag, clt_cache_time,
6635  srv_cache_time, query_timeout, NULL);
6636 
6637 cleanup:
6638  if (server_db_values != NULL)
6639  {
6640  for (i = 0; i < dbval_cnt; i++)
6641  {
6642  db_value_clear (&server_db_values[i]);
6643  }
6644  db_private_free (thread_p, server_db_values);
6645  }
6646 
6647  exit_server (*thread_p);
6648 
6649  return list_id;
6650 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
6651 }
6652 
6653 /*
6654  * qmgr_prepare_and_execute_query -
6655  *
6656  * return:
6657  *
6658  * xasl_stream(in):
6659  * xasl_stream_size(in):
6660  * query_id(in):
6661  * dbval_cnt(in):
6662  * dbval_ptr(in):
6663  * flag(in):
6664  * query_timeout(in):
6665  *
6666  * NOTE:
6667  */
6668 QFILE_LIST_ID *
6669 qmgr_prepare_and_execute_query (char *xasl_stream, int xasl_stream_size, QUERY_ID * query_idp, int dbval_cnt,
6670  DB_VALUE * dbval_ptr, QUERY_FLAG flag, int query_timeout)
6671 {
6672 #if defined(CS_MODE)
6673  QFILE_LIST_ID *regu_result = NULL;
6674  int req_error, senddata_size, replydata_size_listid, replydata_size_page;
6675  int i, size;
6676  char *ptr, *senddata, *replydata;
6677  DB_VALUE *dbval;
6678  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 4) a_request;
6679  char *request;
6680  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 4 + OR_PTR_ALIGNED_SIZE) a_reply;
6681  char *reply;
6682  char *page_ptr;
6683  int page_size, dummy_plan_size;
6684 
6685  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
6686  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
6687 
6688  senddata = NULL;
6689  senddata_size = 0;
6690  for (i = 0, dbval = dbval_ptr; i < dbval_cnt; i++, dbval++)
6691  {
6692  senddata_size += OR_VALUE_ALIGNED_SIZE (dbval);
6693  }
6694 
6695  if (senddata_size != 0)
6696  {
6697  senddata = (char *) malloc (senddata_size);
6698  if (senddata == NULL)
6699  {
6700  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) senddata_size);
6701  return NULL;
6702  }
6703  }
6704 
6705  ptr = or_pack_int (request, dbval_cnt);
6706  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, senddata_size);
6707  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, flag);
6708  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, query_timeout);
6709 
6710  ptr = senddata;
6711  for (i = 0, dbval = dbval_ptr; i < dbval_cnt; i++, dbval++)
6712  {
6713  ptr = or_pack_db_value (ptr, dbval);
6714  }
6715 
6716  /* change senddata_size as real packing size */
6717  senddata_size = CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - senddata);
6718 
6719  req_error = net_client_request_with_callback (NET_SERVER_QM_QUERY_PREPARE_AND_EXECUTE, request,
6720  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
6721  xasl_stream, xasl_stream_size, senddata, senddata_size, &replydata,
6722  &replydata_size_listid, &page_ptr, &replydata_size_page, NULL, NULL);
6723  if (!req_error)
6724  {
6725  /* should be the same as replydata_size */
6726  ptr = or_unpack_int (&reply[OR_INT_SIZE], &size);
6727  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &page_size);
6728  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &dummy_plan_size);
6729  ptr = or_unpack_ptr (ptr, query_idp);
6730 
6731  /* not interested in the return size in the reply buffer, should do some kind of range checking here */
6732  if (replydata != NULL && size)
6733  {
6734  ptr = or_unpack_unbound_listid (replydata, (void **) (&regu_result));
6735  regu_result->last_pgptr = NULL;
6736  if (page_size)
6737  {
6738  regu_result->last_pgptr = page_ptr;
6739  }
6740 
6741  free_and_init (replydata);
6742  }
6743  }
6744 
6745  if (senddata != NULL)
6746  {
6747  free_and_init (senddata);
6748  }
6749 
6750  return regu_result;
6751 #else /* CS_MODE */
6752  QFILE_LIST_ID *regu_result;
6753 
6754  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
6755 
6756  regu_result =
6757  xqmgr_prepare_and_execute_query (thread_p, xasl_stream, xasl_stream_size, query_idp, dbval_cnt, dbval_ptr, &flag,
6758  query_timeout);
6759 
6760  exit_server (*thread_p);
6761 
6762  return regu_result;
6763 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
6764 }
6765 
6766 /*
6767  * qmgr_end_query -
6768  *
6769  * return:
6770  *
6771  * query_id(in):
6772  *
6773  * NOTE:
6774  */
6775 int
6776 qmgr_end_query (QUERY_ID query_id)
6777 {
6778 #if defined(CS_MODE)
6779  int status = ER_FAILED;
6780  int req_error = NO_ERROR;
6781  int i = 0;
6782  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE /* number of query ids */
6783  + OR_PTR_SIZE * NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX /* query ids */
6784  + MAX_ALIGNMENT /* alignment */
6785  )a_request;
6786  char *request = NULL, *ptr = NULL;
6787  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
6788  char *reply = NULL;
6789 
6790  net_Deferred_end_queries[net_Deferred_end_queries_count++] = query_id;
6791  if (net_Deferred_end_queries_count < NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX)
6792  {
6793  /* Do not create a request for now. Defer it until NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX requests are collected or until
6794  * commit/abort. */
6795  return NO_ERROR;
6796  }
6797  assert (net_Deferred_end_queries_count == NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX);
6798  net_Deferred_end_queries_count = 0;
6799 
6800  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
6801  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
6802 
6803  ptr = or_pack_int (request, NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX);
6804  for (i = 0; i < NET_DEFER_END_QUERIES_MAX; i++)
6805  {
6806  ptr = or_pack_ptr (ptr, net_Deferred_end_queries[i]);
6807  }
6808  assert (CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - request) <= (int) OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request));
6809 
6810  req_error =
6811  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_QM_QUERY_END, request, CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - request), reply,
6812  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
6813  if (req_error == NO_ERROR)
6814  {
6815  or_unpack_int (reply, &status);
6816  }
6817  else
6818  {
6819  status = req_error;
6820  }
6821 
6822  return status;
6823 #else /* CS_MODE */
6824  int success = ER_FAILED;
6825 
6826  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
6827 
6828  success = xqmgr_end_query (thread_p, query_id);
6829 
6830  exit_server (*thread_p);
6831 
6832  return success;
6833 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
6834 }

6836 /*
6837  * qm_query_drop_all_plan - Send a SERVER_QM_DROP_ALL_PLAN request to the server
6838  *
6839  * Request the server to clear all XASL cache entires out. When the client
6840  * want to delete all cached query plans, this function will be used.
6841  * This function is a counter part to sqmgr_drop_all_query_plans().
6842  */
6843 /*
6844  * qmgr_drop_all_query_plans -
6845  *
6846  * return:
6847  *
6848  * NOTE:
6849  */
6850 int
6851 qmgr_drop_all_query_plans (void)
6852 {
6853 #if defined(CS_MODE)
6854  int status = ER_FAILED;
6855  int req_error, request_size;
6856  char *request, *reply;
6857  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_XASL_ID_SIZE) a_request;
6858  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
6859 
6860  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
6861  request_size = OR_INT_SIZE;
6862  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
6863 
6864  or_pack_int (request, 0); /* dummy parameter */
6865 
6866  /* send SERVER_QM_QUERY_DROP_ALL_PLANS request with request data; receive status code (int) as a reply */
6867  req_error =
6868  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_QM_QUERY_DROP_ALL_PLANS, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
6869  NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
6870  if (!req_error)
6871  {
6872  /* first argument should be status code (int) */
6873  (void) or_unpack_int (reply, &status);
6874  }
6875 
6876  return status;
6877 #else /* CS_MODE */
6878  int status;
6879 
6880  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
6881 
6882  /* call the server routine of query drop plan */
6883  status = xqmgr_drop_all_query_plans (thread_p);
6884 
6885  exit_server (*thread_p);
6886 
6887  return status;
6888 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
6889 }

7010 int

7052 /*
7053  * serial_get_next_value -
7054  *
7055  * return:
7056  *
7057  * value(in):
7058  * oid(in):
7059  *
7060  * NOTE:
7061  */
7062 int
7063 serial_get_next_value (DB_VALUE * value, OID * oid_p, int cached_num, int num_alloc, int is_auto_increment)
7064 {
7065 #if defined(CS_MODE)
7066  int req_error, error = ER_NET_CLIENT_DATA_RECEIVE;
7067  char *request, *area = NULL;
7068  int area_size;
7069  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_OID_SIZE + (OR_INT_SIZE * 3)) a_request;
7070  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
7071  char *reply, *ptr;
7072 
7073  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
7074  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
7075 
7076  ptr = or_pack_oid (request, oid_p);
7077  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, cached_num);
7078  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, num_alloc);
7079  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, is_auto_increment);
7080 
7081  req_error =
7082  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_QPROC_GET_NEXT_VALUE, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
7083  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &area, &area_size);
7084  if (!req_error && area != NULL)
7085  {
7086  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &area_size);
7087  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &error);
7088  (void) or_unpack_value (area, value);
7089  free_and_init (area);
7090  }
7091 
7092  return error;
7093 #else /* CS_MODE */
7094  int error;
7095 
7096  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
7097 
7098  /*
7099  * If a client wants to generate AUTO_INCREMENT value during client-side
7100  * insertion, a server should update LAST_INSERT_ID on a session.
7101  */
7102  error = xserial_get_next_value (thread_p, value, oid_p, cached_num, num_alloc, is_auto_increment, true);
7103 
7104  exit_server (*thread_p);
7105 
7106  return error;
7107 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
7108 }

7389 /*
7390  * thread_kill_tran_index -
7391  *
7392  * return:
7393  *
7394  * kill_tran_index(in):
7395  * kill_user(in):
7396  * kill_host(in):
7397  * kill_pid(in):
7398  *
7399  * NOTE:
7400  */
7401 int
7402 thread_kill_tran_index (int kill_tran_index, char *kill_user, char *kill_host, int kill_pid)
7403 {
7404 #if defined(CS_MODE)
7405  int success = ER_FAILED;
7406  int request_size, strlen1, strlen2;
7407  char *request;
7408  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
7409  char *reply, *ptr;
7410  int req_error;
7411 
7412  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
7413 
7414  request_size = (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + length_const_string (kill_user, &strlen1)
7415  + length_const_string (kill_host, &strlen2));
7416 
7417  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
7418  if (request == NULL)
7419  {
7420  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
7421  return ER_FAILED;
7422  }
7423 
7424  ptr = or_pack_int (request, kill_tran_index);
7425  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, kill_user, strlen1);
7426  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, kill_host, strlen2);
7427  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, kill_pid);
7428 
7429  req_error = net_client_request (NET_SERVER_CSS_KILL_TRANSACTION, request, request_size, reply,
7430  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
7431  if (!req_error)
7432  {
7433  or_unpack_int (reply, &success);
7434  }
7435 
7436  free_and_init (request);
7437 
7438  return success;
7439 #else /* CS_MODE */
7440  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "css_kill_client: THIS IS ONLY a C/S function");
7441  return ER_FAILED;
7442 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
7443 }

7445 /*
7446  * thread_kill_or_interrupt_tran -
7447  *
7448  * return:
7449  *
7450  * tran_index_list(in):
7451  * num_tran_index(in):
7452  * is_dba_group_member(in):
7453  * interrupt_only(in):
7454  * num_killed(out):
7455  *
7456  * NOTE:
7457  */
7458 int
7459 thread_kill_or_interrupt_tran (int *tran_index_list, int num_tran_index, bool is_dba_group_member, bool interrupt_only,
7460  int *num_killed)
7461 {
7462 #if defined(CS_MODE)
7463  int success = ER_FAILED;
7464  int request_size;
7465  char *request;
7466  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
7467  char *reply, *ptr;
7468  int req_error;
7469  int i;
7470 
7471  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
7472 
7473  request_size = OR_INT_SIZE * (2 + num_tran_index); /* num_tran_index + tran_index_list + interrupt_only */
7474  request_size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* is_dba_group_member */
7475 
7476  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
7477  if (request == NULL)
7478  {
7479  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
7480  return ER_FAILED;
7481  }
7482 
7483  ptr = or_pack_int (request, (int) is_dba_group_member);
7484  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, num_tran_index);
7485 
7486  for (i = 0; i < num_tran_index; i++)
7487  {
7488  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, tran_index_list[i]);
7489  }
7490 
7491  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (interrupt_only) ? 1 : 0);
7492 
7493  req_error =
7494  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_CSS_KILL_OR_INTERRUPT_TRANSACTION, request, request_size, reply,
7495  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
7496 
7497  if (!req_error)
7498  {
7499  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &success);
7500  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, num_killed);
7501  }
7502 
7503  free_and_init (request);
7504 
7505  return success;
7506 #else /* CS_MODE */
7507  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "thread_kill_or_interrupt_tran: THIS IS ONLY a C/S function");
7508  return ER_FAILED;
7509 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
7510 }

7537 /*
7538  * logtb_get_pack_tran_table -
7539  *
7540  * return:
7541  *
7542  * buffer_p(in):
7543  * size_p(in):
7544  * include_query_exec_info(in):
7545  *
7546  * NOTE:
7547  */
7548 int
7549 logtb_get_pack_tran_table (char **buffer_p, int *size_p, bool include_query_exec_info)
7550 {
7551 #if defined(CS_MODE)
7552  int error = NO_ERROR;
7553  int req_error;
7554  int ival;
7555  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
7556  char *request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
7557  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
7558  char *reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
7559  char *ptr;
7560 
7561  /* --query-exec-info */
7562  or_pack_int (request, ((include_query_exec_info) ? 1 : 0));
7563 
7564  req_error =
7565  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_LOG_GETPACK_TRANTB, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
7566  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, buffer_p, size_p);
7567  if (req_error)
7568  {
7569  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7570  error = er_errid ();
7571  }
7572  else
7573  {
7574  /* first word is buffer size, second is error code */
7575  ptr = reply;
7576  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &ival);
7577  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &ival);
7578  error = (int) ival;
7579  }
7580 
7581  return error;
7582 #else /* CS_MODE */
7583  int error;
7584 
7585  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
7586 
7587  error = xlogtb_get_pack_tran_table (thread_p, buffer_p, size_p, 0);
7588 
7589  exit_server (*thread_p);
7590 
7591  return error;
7592 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
7593 }
7594 
7595 /*
7596  * logtb_free_trans_info - Free transaction table information
7597  * return: none
7598  * info(in): TRANS_INFO to be freed
7599  */
7600 void
7601 logtb_free_trans_info (TRANS_INFO * info)
7602 {
7603  int i;
7604 
7605  if (info == NULL)
7606  {
7607  return;
7608  }
7609 
7610  for (i = 0; i < info->num_trans; i++)
7611  {
7612  if (info->tran[i].db_user != NULL)
7613  {
7614  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, info->tran[i].db_user);
7615  }
7616  if (info->tran[i].program_name != NULL)
7617  {
7618  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, info->tran[i].program_name);
7619  }
7620  if (info->tran[i].login_name != NULL)
7621  {
7622  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, info->tran[i].login_name);
7623  }
7624  if (info->tran[i].host_name != NULL)
7625  {
7626  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, info->tran[i].host_name);
7627  }
7628 
7629  if (info->include_query_exec_info)
7630  {
7631  if (info->tran[i].query_exec_info.query_stmt)
7632  {
7633  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, info->tran[i].query_exec_info.query_stmt);
7634  }
7635  if (info->tran[i].query_exec_info.wait_for_tran_index_string)
7636  {
7637  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, info->tran[i].query_exec_info.wait_for_tran_index_string);
7638  }
7639  if (info->tran[i].query_exec_info.sql_id)
7640  {
7641  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, info->tran[i].query_exec_info.sql_id);
7642  }
7643  }
7644  else
7645  {
7646  assert_release (info->tran[i].query_exec_info.query_stmt == NULL);
7647  assert_release (info->tran[i].query_exec_info.wait_for_tran_index_string == NULL);
7648  }
7649  }
7650  free_and_init (info);
7651 }
7652 
7653 /*
7654  * logtb_get_trans_info - Get transaction table information which identifies
7655  * active transactions
7656  * include_query_exec_info(in) :
7657  * return: TRANS_INFO array or NULL
7658  */
7659 TRANS_INFO *
7660 logtb_get_trans_info (bool include_query_exec_info)
7661 {
7662  TRANS_INFO *info = NULL;
7663  char *buffer, *ptr;
7664  int num_trans, bufsize, i;
7665  int error;
7666 
7667  error = logtb_get_pack_tran_table (&buffer, &bufsize, include_query_exec_info);
7668  if (error != NO_ERROR || buffer == NULL)
7669  {
7670  return NULL;
7671  }
7672 
7673  ptr = buffer;
7674  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &num_trans);
7675 
7676  if (num_trans == 0)
7677  {
7678  /* can't happen, there must be at least one transaction */
7679  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
7680  goto error;
7681  }
7682 
7683  i = sizeof (TRANS_INFO) + ((num_trans - 1) * sizeof (ONE_TRAN_INFO));
7684  info = (TRANS_INFO *) malloc (i);
7685  if (info == NULL)
7686  {
7687  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) i);
7688  goto error;
7689  }
7690  memset (info, '\0', i);
7691 
7692  info->num_trans = num_trans;
7693  info->include_query_exec_info = include_query_exec_info;
7694  for (i = 0; i < num_trans; i++)
7695  {
7696  int unpack_int_value;
7697  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &info->tran[i].tran_index);
7698  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &unpack_int_value);
7699  info->tran[i].state = (TRAN_STATE) unpack_int_value;
7700  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &info->tran[i].process_id);
7701  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &info->tran[i].db_user);
7702  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &info->tran[i].program_name);
7703  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &info->tran[i].login_name);
7704  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &info->tran[i].host_name);
7705  if (ptr == NULL)
7706  {
7707  assert (false);
7708  goto error;
7709  }
7710 
7711  if (include_query_exec_info)
7712  {
7713  ptr = or_unpack_float (ptr, &info->tran[i].query_exec_info.query_time);
7714  ptr = or_unpack_float (ptr, &info->tran[i].query_exec_info.tran_time);
7715  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &info->tran[i].query_exec_info.wait_for_tran_index_string);
7716  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &info->tran[i].query_exec_info.query_stmt);
7717  ptr = or_unpack_string (ptr, &info->tran[i].query_exec_info.sql_id);
7718  if (ptr == NULL)
7719  {
7720  assert (false);
7721  goto error;
7722  }
7723  OR_UNPACK_XASL_ID (ptr, &info->tran[i].query_exec_info.xasl_id);
7724  }
7725  }
7726 
7727  if (((int) (ptr - buffer)) != bufsize)
7728  {
7729  /* unpacking didn't match size, garbage */
7730  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
7731  goto error;
7732  }
7733 
7734  free_and_init (buffer);
7735 
7736  return info;
7737 
7738 error:
7739  if (buffer != NULL)
7740  {
7741  free_and_init (buffer);
7742  }
7743 
7744  if (info != NULL)

7836 /*
7837  * btree_get_statistics -
7838  *
7839  * return:
7840  *
7841  * btid(in):
7842  * stat_info(in):
7843  *
7844  * NOTE:
7845  */
7846 int
7847 btree_get_statistics (BTID * btid, BTREE_STATS * stat_info)
7848 {
7849 #if defined(CS_MODE)
7850  int req_error, status = ER_FAILED;
7851  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE) a_request;
7852  char *request;
7853  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 5) a_reply;
7854  char *reply;
7855  char *ptr;
7856 
7857  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
7858  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
7859 
7860  ptr = or_pack_btid (request, btid);
7861 
7862  req_error =
7863  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_BTREE_GET_STATISTICS, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
7864  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
7865  if (!req_error)
7866  {
7867  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &status);
7868  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &stat_info->leafs);
7869  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &stat_info->pages);
7870  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &stat_info->height);
7871  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &stat_info->keys);
7872 
7873  assert_release (stat_info->leafs > 0);
7874  assert_release (stat_info->pages > 0);
7875  assert_release (stat_info->height > 0);
7876  assert_release (stat_info->keys >= 0);
7877  }
7878 
7879  return status;
7880 #else /* CS_MODE */
7881  int success = ER_FAILED;
7882 
7883  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
7884 
7885  assert_release (!BTID_IS_NULL (btid));
7886  assert_release (stat_info->keys == 0);
7887  assert_release (stat_info->pkeys_size == 0);
7888  assert_release (stat_info->pkeys == NULL);
7889 
7890  BTID_COPY (&stat_info->btid, btid);
7891  if (stat_info->pkeys_size != 0)
7892  {
7893  stat_info->pkeys_size = 0; /* do not request pkeys info */
7894  }
7895 
7896  success = btree_get_stats (thread_p, stat_info, STATS_WITH_SAMPLING);
7897 
7898  assert_release (stat_info->leafs > 0);
7899  assert_release (stat_info->pages > 0);
7900  assert_release (stat_info->height > 0);
7901  assert_release (stat_info->keys >= 0);
7902 
7903  exit_server (*thread_p);
7904 
7905  return success;
7906 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
7907 }

7909 /*
7910  * btree_get_index_key_type () - Get index key type.
7911  *
7912  * return : Error code.
7913  * btid (in) : Index b-tree identifier.
7914  * key_type_p (out) : Index key type.
7915  */
7916 int
7917 btree_get_index_key_type (BTID btid, TP_DOMAIN ** key_type_p)
7918 {
7919 #if defined(CS_MODE)
7920  int error;
7921  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE) a_request;
7922  char *request;
7923  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_reply;
7924  char *reply = NULL;
7925  char *ptr = NULL;
7926  char *reply_data = NULL;
7927  int reply_data_size = 0;
7928  int dummy;
7929 
7930  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
7931  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
7932 
7933  /* Send BTID to server */
7934  ptr = or_pack_btid (request, &btid);
7935 
7936  error =
7937  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_BTREE_GET_KEY_TYPE, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
7938  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &reply_data, &reply_data_size);
7939  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7940  {
7941  return error;
7942  }
7943  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &reply_data_size);
7944  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &error);
7945  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7946  {
7947  return error;
7948  }
7949  if (reply_data != NULL)
7950  {
7951  /* Obtain key type from server */
7952  (void) or_unpack_domain (reply_data, key_type_p, &dummy);
7953  }
7954  free_and_init (reply_data);
7955 
7956  return error;
7957 #else /* CS_MODE */
7958  int error = NO_ERROR;
7959 
7960  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
7961 
7962  assert_release (!BTID_IS_NULL (&btid));
7963  assert_release (key_type_p != NULL);
7964 
7965  error = xbtree_get_key_type (thread_p, btid, key_type_p);
7966 
7967  exit_server (*thread_p);
7968 
7969  return error;
7970 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
7971 }

8017 /*
8018  * qp_get_server_info -
8019  *
8020  * return:
8021  *
8022  * server_info(in):
8023  *
8024  * NOTE:
8025  */
8026 int
8027 qp_get_server_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, int server_info_bits)
8028 {
8029 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8030  int status = ER_FAILED;
8031  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_request;
8032  char *request;
8033  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
8034  char *reply;
8035  char *ptr, *area = NULL;
8036  int val_size;
8037 
8038  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
8039  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8040 
8041  ptr = or_pack_int (request, server_info_bits);
8042 
8043  status =
8044  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_QPROC_GET_SERVER_INFO, request, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply,
8045  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &area, &val_size);
8046  if (status != NO_ERROR)
8047  {
8048  goto error_exit;
8049  }
8050 
8051  if (area != NULL)
8052  {
8053  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &val_size);
8054  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &status);
8055 
8056  if (status != NO_ERROR)
8057  {
8058  goto error_exit;
8059  }
8060 
8061  ptr = area;
8062  if (server_info_bits & SI_SYS_DATETIME)
8063  {
8064  ptr = or_unpack_value (ptr, &(parser->sys_datetime));
8065  ptr = or_unpack_value (ptr, &(parser->sys_epochtime));
8066  }
8067  if (server_info_bits & SI_LOCAL_TRANSACTION_ID)
8068  {
8069  ptr = or_unpack_value (ptr, &parser->local_transaction_id);
8070  }
8071  }
8072 
8073 error_exit:
8074  if (area != NULL)
8075  {
8076  free_and_init (area);
8077  }
8078 
8079  return status;
8080 #else /* CS_MODE */
8081  int success = NO_ERROR;
8082 
8083  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
8084 
8085  if (server_info_bits & SI_SYS_DATETIME)
8086  {
8087  success = db_sys_date_and_epoch_time (&(parser->sys_datetime), &(parser->sys_epochtime));
8088  if (success != NO_ERROR)
8089  {
8090  goto error_exit;
8091  }
8092  }
8093 
8094  if (server_info_bits & SI_LOCAL_TRANSACTION_ID)
8095  {
8096  success = db_local_transaction_id (&parser->local_transaction_id);
8097  }
8098 
8099 error_exit:
8100  exit_server (*thread_p);
8101  return success;
8102 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8103 }

8105 /*
8106  * sysprm_change_server_parameters () - Sends a list of assignments to server in order to change system parameter
8107  * values.
8108  *
8109  * return : SYSPRM_ERR code.
8110  * assignments (in) : list of assignments.
8111  */
8112 SYSPRM_ERR
8113 sysprm_change_server_parameters (const SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE * assignments)
8114 {
8115 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8116  SYSPRM_ERR rc = PRM_ERR_COMM_ERR;
8117  int request_size = 0, req_error = NO_ERROR;
8118  char *request = NULL, *reply = NULL;
8119  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
8120 
8121  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8122 
8123  request_size = sysprm_packed_assign_values_length (assignments, 0);
8124  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
8125  if (request == NULL)
8126  {
8127  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
8128  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
8129  }
8130 
8131  (void) sysprm_pack_assign_values (request, assignments);
8132  req_error =
8133  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_PRM_SET_PARAMETERS, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply),
8134  NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
8135  if (req_error == NO_ERROR)
8136  {
8137  int unpack_value;
8138  or_unpack_int (reply, &unpack_value);
8139  rc = (SYSPRM_ERR) unpack_value;
8140  }
8141  else
8142  {
8143  rc = PRM_ERR_COMM_ERR;
8144  }
8145 
8146  free_and_init (request);
8147 
8148  return rc;
8149 #else /* CS_MODE */
8150  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
8151  xsysprm_change_server_parameters (assignments);
8152  exit_server (*thread_p);
8153 
8154  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8155 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8156 }
8157 
8158 /*
8159  * sysprm_obtain_server_parameters () - Obtain values for system parameters from server.
8160  *
8161  * return : SYSPRM_ERR code.
8162  * prm_values_ptr (in/out) : list of parameter values.
8163  */
8164 SYSPRM_ERR
8165 sysprm_obtain_server_parameters (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE ** prm_values_ptr)
8166 {
8167 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8168  SYSPRM_ERR rc = PRM_ERR_COMM_ERR;
8169  int req_error = NO_ERROR, request_size = 0, receive_size = 0;
8170  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_reply;
8171  char *reply = NULL, *request_data = NULL, *receive_data = NULL;
8172  char *ptr = NULL;
8173  SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE *updated_prm_values = NULL;
8174 
8175  assert (prm_values_ptr != NULL && *prm_values_ptr != NULL);
8176 
8177  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8178 
8179  request_size = sysprm_packed_assign_values_length (*prm_values_ptr, 0);
8180  request_data = (char *) malloc (request_size);
8181  if (request_data == NULL)
8182  {
8183  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
8184  return PRM_ERR_NO_MEM_FOR_PRM;
8185  }
8186 
8187  (void) sysprm_pack_assign_values (request_data, *prm_values_ptr);
8188  req_error =
8189  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_PRM_GET_PARAMETERS, request_data, request_size, reply,
8190  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &receive_data, &receive_size);
8191  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
8192  {
8193  rc = PRM_ERR_COMM_ERR;
8194  }
8195  else
8196  {
8197  int unpack_value;
8198  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &receive_size);
8199  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &unpack_value);
8200  rc = (SYSPRM_ERR) unpack_value;
8201  if (rc != PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR || receive_data == NULL)
8202  {
8203  goto cleanup;
8204  }
8205 
8206  (void) sysprm_unpack_assign_values (receive_data, &updated_prm_values);
8207 
8208  /* free old values */
8209  sysprm_free_assign_values (prm_values_ptr);
8210  /* update values */
8211  *prm_values_ptr = updated_prm_values;
8212  }
8213 
8214 cleanup:
8215  if (request_data != NULL)
8216  {
8217  free_and_init (request_data);
8218  }
8219 
8220  if (receive_data != NULL)
8221  {
8222  free_and_init (receive_data);
8223  }
8224 
8225  return rc;
8226 #else /* CS_MODE */
8227  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
8228  xsysprm_obtain_server_parameters (*prm_values_ptr);
8229  exit_server (*thread_p);
8230 
8231  return PRM_ERR_NO_ERROR;
8232 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8233 }
8234 
8235 /*
8236  * sysprm_get_force_server_parameters () - Get from server values for system parameters marked with
8237  * PRM_FORCE_SERVER flag.
8238  *
8239  * return : error code
8240  * change_values (out) : list of parameter values.
8241  */
8242 int
8243 sysprm_get_force_server_parameters (SYSPRM_ASSIGN_VALUE ** change_values)
8244 {
8245 #if defined (CS_MODE)
8246  int req_error;
8247  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_reply;
8248  int area_size, error;
8249  char *reply = NULL, *area = NULL, *ptr = NULL;
8250 
8251  assert (change_values != NULL);
8252  *change_values = NULL;
8253 
8254  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8255 
8256  req_error =
8257  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_PRM_GET_FORCE_PARAMETERS, NULL, 0, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0,
8258  &area, &area_size);
8259  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
8260  {
8261  error = req_error;
8262  goto error;
8263  }
8264 
8265  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &area_size);
8266  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &error);
8267  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8268  {
8269  goto error;
8270  }
8271 
8272  if (area != NULL)
8273  {
8274  (void) sysprm_unpack_assign_values (area, change_values);
8275  free_and_init (area);
8276  }
8277 
8278  return NO_ERROR;
8279 
8280 error:
8281  if (area != NULL)
8282  {
8283  free_and_init (area);
8284  }
8285 
8286  return error;
8287 #else /* CS_MODE */
8288  assert (change_values != NULL);
8289  *change_values = NULL;
8290  return NO_ERROR;
8291 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8292 }

8405 #endif /* !CS_MODE */

8460 /*
8461  * repl_set_info -
8462  *
8463  * return:
8464  *
8465  * repl_info(in):
8466  *
8467  * NOTE:
8468  */
8469 int
8470 repl_set_info (REPL_INFO * repl_info)
8471 {
8472 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8473  int req_error, success = ER_FAILED;
8474  int request_size = 0, strlen1, strlen2, strlen3, strlen4;
8475  char *request = NULL, *ptr;
8476  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
8477  char *reply;
8478  REPL_INFO_SBR *repl_schema;
8479 
8480  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8481 
8482  switch (repl_info->repl_info_type)
8483  {
8484  case REPL_INFO_TYPE_SBR:
8485  repl_schema = (REPL_INFO_SBR *) repl_info->info;
8486  request_size = (OR_INT_SIZE /* REPL_INFO.REPL_INFO_TYPE */
8487  + OR_INT_SIZE /* REPL_INFO_SCHEMA.statement_type */
8488  + length_const_string (repl_schema->name, &strlen1)
8489  + length_const_string (repl_schema->stmt_text, &strlen2)
8490  + length_const_string (repl_schema->db_user, &strlen3)
8491  + length_const_string (repl_schema->sys_prm_context, &strlen4));
8492 
8493  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
8494  if (request == NULL)
8495  {
8496  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
8497  return ER_FAILED;
8498  }
8499 
8500  ptr = or_pack_int (request, REPL_INFO_TYPE_SBR);
8501  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, repl_schema->statement_type);
8502  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, repl_schema->name, strlen1);
8503  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, repl_schema->stmt_text, strlen2);
8504  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, repl_schema->db_user, strlen3);
8505  ptr = pack_const_string_with_length (ptr, repl_schema->sys_prm_context, strlen4);
8506  req_error =
8507  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_REPL_INFO, request, request_size, reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL,
8508  0, NULL, 0);
8509  if (!req_error)
8510  {
8511  or_unpack_int (reply, &success);
8512  }
8513 
8514  free_and_init (request);
8515  break;
8516 
8517  default:
8518  break;
8519  }
8520 
8521  return success;
8522 #else /* CS_MODE */
8523  int r = ER_FAILED;
8524 
8525  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
8526  r = xrepl_set_info (thread_p, repl_info);
8527  exit_server (*thread_p);
8528  return r;
8529 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8530 }

8532 /*
8533  * locator_check_fk_validity -
8534  *
8535  * return:
8536  *
8537  * cls_oid(in):
8538  * hfid(in):
8539  * key_type(in):
8540  * n_attrs(in):
8541  * attr_ids(in):
8542  * pk_cls_oid(in):
8543  * pk_btid(in):
8544  * fk_name(in):
8545  *
8546  * NOTE:
8547  */
8548 int
8549 locator_check_fk_validity (OID * cls_oid, HFID * hfid, TP_DOMAIN * key_type, int n_attrs, int *attr_ids,
8550  OID * pk_cls_oid, BTID * pk_btid, char *fk_name)
8551 {
8552 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8553  int error, req_error, request_size, domain_size;
8554  char *ptr;
8555  char *request;
8556  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
8557  char *reply;
8558  int i, strlen;
8559 
8560  error = NO_ERROR;
8561  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8562 
8563  domain_size = or_packed_domain_size (key_type, 0);
8564  request_size = (OR_OID_SIZE + OR_HFID_SIZE + domain_size + OR_INT_SIZE + (n_attrs * OR_INT_SIZE)
8565  + OR_OID_SIZE + OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE + or_packed_string_length (fk_name, &strlen));
8566 
8567  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
8568  if (request == NULL)
8569  {
8570  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
8571  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8572  }
8573 
8574  ptr = or_pack_oid (request, cls_oid);
8575  ptr = or_pack_hfid (ptr, hfid);
8576  ptr = or_pack_domain (ptr, key_type, 0, 0);
8577  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, n_attrs);
8578  for (i = 0; i < n_attrs; i++)
8579  {
8580  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, attr_ids[i]);
8581  }
8582  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, pk_cls_oid);
8583  ptr = or_pack_btid (ptr, pk_btid);
8584  ptr = or_pack_string_with_length (ptr, fk_name, strlen);
8585 
8586  req_error = net_client_request (NET_SERVER_LC_CHECK_FK_VALIDITY, request, request_size, reply,
8587  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
8588  if (!req_error)
8589  {
8590  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &error);
8591  }
8592 
8593  free_and_init (request);
8594 
8595  return error;
8596 #else /* CS_MODE */
8597  int error = NO_ERROR;
8598 
8599  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p = enter_server ();
8600 
8601  error =
8602  xlocator_check_fk_validity (thread_p, cls_oid, hfid, key_type, n_attrs, attr_ids, pk_cls_oid, pk_btid, fk_name);
8603 
8604  exit_server (*thread_p);
8605  return error;
8606 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8607 }

8609 /*
8610  * logwr_get_log_pages -
8611  *
8612  * return:
8613  *
8614  * rc_ptr(in/out): request context
8615  *
8616  * NOTE:
8617  */
8618 int
8619 logwr_get_log_pages (LOGWR_CONTEXT * ctx_ptr)
8620 {
8621 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8622  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT64_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_request;
8623  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_reply;
8624  char *request, *reply;
8625  char *replydata1, *replydata2;
8626  int replydata_size1, replydata_size2;
8627  char *ptr;
8628  LOG_PAGEID first_pageid_torecv;
8629  LOGWR_MODE mode, save_mode;
8630  int req_error, error = NO_ERROR;
8631 
8632  /* Do it as async mode at the first request to the server. And, if several pages are left to get, keep it as async
8633  * mode */
8634 
8635  assert (logwr_Gl.last_recv_pageid <= logwr_Gl.hdr.eof_lsa.pageid);
8636  if (logwr_Gl.last_recv_pageid == logwr_Gl.hdr.eof_lsa.pageid)
8637  {
8638  /* In case of synchronous request */
8639  first_pageid_torecv = logwr_Gl.last_recv_pageid;
8640 
8641  mode = (logwr_Gl.last_recv_pageid == NULL_PAGEID) ? LOGWR_MODE_ASYNC : logwr_Gl.mode;
8642  }
8643  else
8644  {
8645  /* In the middle of sending the pages which are already flushed */
8646  if (logwr_Gl.last_recv_pageid == NULL_PAGEID)
8647  {
8648  /* To check database equality at first, get the header page */
8649  first_pageid_torecv = LOGPB_HEADER_PAGE_ID;
8650  }
8651  else
8652  {
8653  /* When it overtakes the state of the server, it set ha_file_state is sync'ed. And, the flush action is not
8654  * sync'ed with the server. So, it requests the last page again to get the missing log records. */
8655  if (logwr_Gl.hdr.ha_file_status == LOG_HA_FILESTAT_SYNCHRONIZED)
8656  {
8657  first_pageid_torecv = logwr_Gl.last_recv_pageid;
8658  }
8659  else
8660  {
8661  first_pageid_torecv = logwr_Gl.last_recv_pageid + 1;
8662  }
8663  }
8664  /* In case of archiving, not replication delay */
8665  if (first_pageid_torecv == logwr_Gl.ori_nxarv_pageid)
8666  {
8667  mode = logwr_Gl.mode;
8668  }
8669  else
8670  {
8671  mode = LOGWR_MODE_ASYNC;
8672  }
8673  }
8674 
8675  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "logwr_get_log_pages, fpageid(%lld), mode(%s)", first_pageid_torecv,
8676  mode == LOGWR_MODE_SYNC ? "sync" : (mode == LOGWR_MODE_ASYNC ? "async" : "semisync"));
8677 
8678  save_mode = logwr_Gl.mode;
8679  logwr_Gl.mode = mode;
8680 
8681  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
8682  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8683 
8684  if (first_pageid_torecv == NULL_PAGEID && logwr_Gl.start_pageid >= NULL_PAGEID)
8685  {
8686  ptr = or_pack_int64 (request, logwr_Gl.start_pageid);
8687  mode = (LOGWR_MODE) (mode | LOGWR_COPY_FROM_FIRST_PHY_PAGE_MASK);
8688  }
8689  else
8690  {
8691  ptr = or_pack_int64 (request, first_pageid_torecv);
8692  }
8693 
8694  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, mode);
8695  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, ctx_ptr->last_error);
8696 
8697  req_error =
8698  net_client_request_with_logwr_context (ctx_ptr, NET_SERVER_LOGWR_GET_LOG_PAGES, request,
8699  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_request), reply, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL,
8700  0, NULL, 0, &replydata1, &replydata_size1, &replydata2, &replydata_size2);
8701 
8702  logwr_Gl.mode = save_mode;
8703 
8704  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
8705  {
8706  error = req_error;
8707  if (error == ER_NET_SERVER_CRASHED)
8708  {
8709  if (logwr_Gl.mode == LOGWR_MODE_SEMISYNC)
8710  {
8711  logwr_Gl.force_flush = true;
8712  logwr_write_log_pages ();
8713  }
8714  /* Write the server is dead at the log header */
8715  logwr_Gl.hdr.ha_server_state = HA_SERVER_STATE_DEAD;
8716  logwr_flush_header_page ();
8717  ctx_ptr->shutdown = true;
8718  }
8719  else if (error == ER_HA_LW_FAILED_GET_LOG_PAGE)
8720  {
8721  if (logwr_Gl.mode == LOGWR_MODE_SEMISYNC)
8722  {
8723  logwr_Gl.force_flush = true;
8724  logwr_write_log_pages ();
8725  }
8726 
8727  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, first_pageid_torecv);
8728 
8729  ctx_ptr->shutdown = true;
8730  }
8731  }
8732 
8733  if (logwr_Gl.start_pageid >= NULL_PAGEID && logwr_Gl.hdr.eof_lsa.pageid == logwr_Gl.hdr.append_lsa.pageid
8734  && logwr_Gl.hdr.ha_file_status == LOG_HA_FILESTAT_SYNCHRONIZED)
8735  {
8736  ctx_ptr->shutdown = true;
8737  error = NO_ERROR;
8738  }
8739 
8740  return error;
8741 
8742 #else /* CS_MODE */
8743  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_NOT_IN_STANDALONE, 1, "copylog database");
8744  return ER_NOT_IN_STANDALONE;
8745 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8746 }

8812 /*
8813  * boot_compact_classes () - compact specified classes
8814  *
8815  * return : NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
8816  *
8817  * class_oids(in): the class oids list to process
8818  * n_classes(in): the length of class_oids
8819  * space_to_process(in): the maximum space to process
8820  * instance_lock_timeout(in): the lock timeout for instances
8821  * class_lock_timeout(in): the lock timeout for classes
8822  * delete_old_repr(in): true if old class representations must be deleted
8823  * last_processed_class_oid(in,out): last processed class oid
8824  * last_processed_oid(in,out): last processed oid
8825  * total_objects(in,out): count processed objects for each class
8826  * failed_objects(in,out): count failed objects for each class
8827  * modified_objects(in,out): count modified objects for each class
8828  * big_objects(in,out): count big objects for each class
8829  * initial_last_repr_id(in,out): the list of last class representation
8830  *
8831  * Note:
8832  */
8833 int
8834 boot_compact_classes (OID ** class_oids, int num_classes, int space_to_process, int instance_lock_timeout,
8835  int class_lock_timeout, bool delete_old_repr, OID * last_processed_class_oid,
8836  OID * last_processed_oid, int *total_objects, int *failed_objects, int *modified_objects,
8837  int *big_objects, int *ids_repr)
8838 {
8839 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8840  int success = ER_FAILED, request_size, req_error, i, reply_size;
8841  char *reply = NULL, *request = NULL, *ptr = NULL;
8842 
8843  if (class_oids == NULL || num_classes < 0 || space_to_process < 0 || last_processed_class_oid == NULL
8844  || last_processed_oid == NULL || total_objects == NULL || failed_objects == NULL || modified_objects == NULL
8845  || big_objects == NULL || ids_repr == NULL)
8846  {
8847  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_PARAMETER;
8848  }
8849 
8850  request_size = OR_OID_SIZE * (num_classes + 2) + OR_INT_SIZE * (5 * num_classes + 5);
8851 
8852  request = (char *) malloc (request_size);
8853  if (request == NULL)
8854  {
8855  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) request_size);
8856  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8857  }
8858 
8859  reply_size = OR_OID_SIZE * 2 + OR_INT_SIZE * (5 * num_classes + 1);
8860  reply = (char *) malloc (reply_size);
8861  if (reply == NULL)
8862  {
8863  free_and_init (request);
8864  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) reply_size);
8865  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8866  }
8867 
8868  ptr = or_pack_int (request, num_classes);
8869  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8870  {
8871  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, class_oids[i]);
8872  }
8873 
8874  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, space_to_process);
8875  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, instance_lock_timeout);
8876  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, class_lock_timeout);
8877  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, (int) delete_old_repr);
8878  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, last_processed_class_oid);
8879  ptr = or_pack_oid (ptr, last_processed_oid);
8880 
8881  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8882  {
8883  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, total_objects[i]);
8884  }
8885 
8886  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8887  {
8888  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, failed_objects[i]);
8889  }
8890 
8891  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8892  {
8893  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, modified_objects[i]);
8894  }
8895 
8896  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8897  {
8898  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, big_objects[i]);
8899  }
8900 
8901  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8902  {
8903  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, ids_repr[i]);
8904  }
8905 
8906  req_error = net_client_request (NET_SERVER_BO_COMPACT_DB, request, request_size, reply, reply_size, NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
8907  if (!req_error)
8908  {
8909  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &success);
8910  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, last_processed_class_oid);
8911  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, last_processed_oid);
8912 
8913  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8914  {
8915  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, total_objects + i);
8916  }
8917 
8918  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8919  {
8920  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, failed_objects + i);
8921  }
8922 
8923  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8924  {
8925  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, modified_objects + i);
8926  }
8927 
8928  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8929  {
8930  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, big_objects + i);
8931  }
8932 
8933  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; i++)
8934  {
8935  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, ids_repr + i);
8936  }
8937  }
8938 
8939  free_and_init (request);
8940  free_and_init (reply);
8941 
8942  return success;
8943 #else /* CS_MODE */
8944  return ER_FAILED;
8945 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8946 }

8948 /*
8949  * boot_heap_compact () - compact heap file of gived class
8950  *
8951  * return : NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
8952  *
8953  * class_oid(in): the class oid of heap to compact
8954  *
8955  * Note:
8956  */
8957 int
8958 boot_heap_compact (OID * class_oid)
8959 {
8960 #if defined(CS_MODE)
8961  int success = ER_FAILED, request_size, req_error, reply_size;
8962 
8963  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_OID_SIZE) a_request;
8964  char *request;
8965  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
8966  char *reply;
8967 
8968  if (class_oid == NULL)
8969  {
8970  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_PARAMETER;
8971  }
8972 
8973  request = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_request);
8974  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
8975 
8976  request_size = OR_OID_SIZE;
8977  reply_size = OR_INT_SIZE;
8978 
8979  or_pack_oid (request, class_oid);
8980 
8981  req_error =
8982  net_client_request (NET_SERVER_BO_HEAP_COMPACT, request, request_size, reply, reply_size, NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
8983  if (!req_error)
8984  {
8985  (void) or_unpack_int (reply, &success);
8986  }
8987 
8988  return success;
8989 #else /* CS_MODE */
8990  return ER_FAILED;
8991 #endif /* !CS_MODE */
8992 }

8994 /*
8995  * compact_db_start () - start database compaction
8996  *
8997  * return : error code
8998  *
8999  */
9000 int
9001 compact_db_start (void)
9002 {
9003 #if defined(CS_MODE)
9004  int success = ER_FAILED, req_error, reply_size;
9005  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE) a_reply;
9006  char *reply;
9007 
9008  reply_size = OR_INT_SIZE;

9490 /*
9491  * boot_get_server_locales () - get information about server locales
9492  *
9493  * return : error code or no error
9494  */
9495 int
9496 boot_get_server_locales (LANG_COLL_COMPAT ** server_collations, LANG_LOCALE_COMPAT ** server_locales,
9497  int *server_coll_cnt, int *server_locales_cnt)
9498 {
9499 #if defined(CS_MODE)
9500  int req_error;
9501  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_reply;
9502  char *reply = NULL;
9503  char *reply_data = NULL;
9504  char *ptr = NULL;
9505  int reply_size = 0, temp_int, i, dummy;
9506  char *temp_str;
9507  size_t size;
9508 
9509  assert (server_collations != NULL);
9510  assert (server_locales != NULL);
9511  assert (server_coll_cnt != NULL);
9512  assert (server_locales_cnt != NULL);
9513 
9514  *server_collations = NULL;
9515  *server_locales = NULL;
9516  *server_coll_cnt = 0;
9517  *server_locales_cnt = 0;
9518 
9519  req_error =
9520  net_client_request2 (NET_SERVER_BO_GET_LOCALES_INFO, NULL, 0, OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply),
9521  OR_ALIGNED_BUF_SIZE (a_reply), NULL, 0, &reply_data, &reply_size);
9522  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
9523  {
9524  goto error;
9525  }
9526 
9527  reply = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_reply);
9528  /* unpack data size */
9529  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply, &dummy);
9530  /* unpack error code */
9531  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &req_error);
9532  if (req_error != NO_ERROR)
9533  {
9534  goto error;
9535  }
9536 
9537  assert (req_error == NO_ERROR);
9538  assert (reply_data != NULL);
9539 
9540  ptr = or_unpack_int (reply_data, server_coll_cnt);
9541  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, server_locales_cnt);
9542 
9543  size = (*server_coll_cnt * sizeof (LANG_COLL_COMPAT));
9544  *server_collations = (LANG_COLL_COMPAT *) malloc (size);
9545  if (*server_collations == NULL)
9546  {
9547  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) size);
9548  req_error = ER_FAILED;
9549  goto error;
9550  }
9551 
9552  size = (*server_locales_cnt * sizeof (LANG_LOCALE_COMPAT));
9553  *server_locales = (LANG_LOCALE_COMPAT *) malloc (size);
9554  if (*server_locales == NULL)
9555  {
9556  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) size);
9557  req_error = ER_FAILED;
9558  goto error;
9559  }
9560 
9561  for (i = 0; i < *server_coll_cnt; i++)
9562  {
9563  LANG_COLL_COMPAT *ref_coll = &((*server_collations)[i]);
9564 
9565  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &(ref_coll->coll_id));
9566 
9567  ptr = or_unpack_string_nocopy (ptr, &(temp_str));
9568  strncpy (ref_coll->coll_name, temp_str, sizeof (ref_coll->coll_name) - 1);
9569  ref_coll->coll_name[sizeof (ref_coll->coll_name) - 1] = '\0';
9570 
9571  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &(temp_int));
9572  ref_coll->codeset = (INTL_CODESET) temp_int;
9573 
9574  ptr = or_unpack_string_nocopy (ptr, &(temp_str));
9575  strncpy (ref_coll->checksum, temp_str, sizeof (ref_coll->checksum) - 1);
9576  ref_coll->checksum[sizeof (ref_coll->checksum) - 1] = '\0';
9577  }
9578 
9579  for (i = 0; i < *server_locales_cnt; i++)
9580  {
9581  LANG_LOCALE_COMPAT *ref_loc = &((*server_locales)[i]);
9582 
9583  ptr = or_unpack_string_nocopy (ptr, &(temp_str));
9584  strncpy (ref_loc->lang_name, temp_str, sizeof (ref_loc->lang_name) - 1);
9585  ref_loc->lang_name[sizeof (ref_loc->lang_name) - 1] = '\0';
9586 
9587  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &(temp_int));
9588  ref_loc->codeset = (INTL_CODESET) temp_int;
9589 
9590  ptr = or_unpack_string_nocopy (ptr, &(temp_str));
9591  strncpy (ref_loc->checksum, temp_str, sizeof (ref_loc->checksum) - 1);
9592  ref_loc->checksum[sizeof (ref_loc->checksum) - 1] = '\0';
9593  }
9594 
9595  if (reply_data != NULL)
9596  {
9597  free_and_init (reply_data);
9598  }
9599  return req_error;
9600 
9601 error:
9602  if (reply_data != NULL)
9603  {
9604  free_and_init (reply_data);
9605  }
9606 
9607  return req_error;
9608 #else
9609  return -1;
9610 #endif
9611 }

9613 /*
9614  * tran_lock_rep_read () - Lock the object that is common to all RR transactions
9615  * return : NO_ERROR if all OK, error status otherwise
9616  * lock_rr_tran(in) : type of lock
9617  *
9618  * Note: This is used in ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN ... NOT NULL scenarios
9619  */
9620 int
9621 tran_lock_rep_read (LOCK lock_rr_tran)
9622 {
9623 #if defined(CS_MODE)
9624  int req_error;

9657  * return : error code or no error
9658  */
9659 int
9660 boot_get_server_timezone_checksum (char *timezone_checksum)
9661 {
9662 #if defined(CS_MODE)
9663  int req_error;
9664  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (OR_INT_SIZE * 2) a_reply;

9676  goto error;

9685  {

9690

9694 
9695  if (reply_data != NULL)

9697  free_and_init (reply_data);

9699  return req_error;
9700 
9701 error:
9702  if (reply_data != NULL)
9703  {
9704  free_and_init (reply_data);
9705  }
